TIME_TO_FIRST_CLICK_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_INTERACTION_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click, key, mouse or scroll event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_KEY_INPUT_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next key event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next mouse move event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_SCROLL_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next scroll event per top-level content browsing context.

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to be aborted due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down).

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to complete, given that it failed.

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to complete, given that DTLS succeeded.

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to be aborted due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down).

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to complete, given that it failed.

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to complete, given that DTLS succeeded.

SSL_HANDSHAKE_RESULT.description: SSL handshake result, 0=success, 1-255=NSS error offset, 256-511=SEC error offset + 256, 512-639=NSPR error offset + 512, 640-670=PKIX error, 671=unknown err

AUSHELPER_CPU_ERROR_CODE.description: The error code from the aushelper system add-on when querying the registry for CPU information for bug 1296630 (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

AUSHELPER_CPU_RESULT_CODE.description: Whether the system is affected by bug 1296630 (1=No, 2=Yes, 3=Error, and 4=Unknown).

AUSHELPER_WEBSENSE_ERROR_CODE.description: The error code from the aushelper system add-on when gathering information on Websense (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

AUSHELPER_WEBSENSE_REG_EXISTS.description: Whether the system has a Websense InstallVersion registry value (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

URLCLASSIFIER_NEGATIVE_CACHE_DURATION.description: Negative cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider

URLCLASSIFIER_POSITIVE_CACHE_DURATION.description: Positive cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider

SSL_CT_POLICY_COMPLIANCE_OF_EV_CERTS.description: Certificate Transparency Policy compliance of successfully established SSL connections with EV certificate (1=Compliant, 2=Insufficient number of SCTs, 3=Insufficient diversity of CT Log operators)

SSL_CT_POLICY_COMPLIANT_CONNECTIONS_BY_C.description: Number of successfully established TLS connections compliant with the Certificate Transparency Policy, by CA. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/security/manager/ssl/RootHashes.inc for names of CAs. Bucket zero holds CAs not present in the list.

SSL_CT_POLICY_NON_COMPLIANT_CONNECTIONS_.description: Number of successfully established TLS connections NOT compliant with the Certificate Transparency Policy, by CA. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/security/manager/ssl/RootHashes.inc for names of CAs. Bucket zero holds CAs not present in the list.

URLCLASSIFIER_MATCH_RESULT.description: The result of each URL lookup against both google and google4 lists. (0 = no match, 1 = V2 prefix only, 2 = V4 prefix only, 3 = V2 and V4 prefixes, 4 = V2 and V4 completions, 5 = V2 completion only, 6 = V4 completion only, 7 = V2 completion and v4 prefix, 8 = V2 prefix and V4 completion, 9 = unexpected result)

APPLICATION_REPUTATION_ALLOWLIST_MATCH.description: For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of the allow list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)

APPLICATION_REPUTATION_BLOCKLIST_MATCH.description: For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of block list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_DURATION.description: Duration of animations running on the compositor in milliseconds

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_MAX_LAYER_AREA.description: High-watermark of layer area affected during a compositor animation. Units are layer pixels squared.

FENNEC_SESSIONSTORE_ALL_FILES_DAMAGED.description: Both the main session file and its backup could not be read and and the first run pref is false.

EXTENSION_INSTALL_PROMPT_RESULT.description: Results of displaying add-on installation notifications.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to abort ICE due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down). Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to complete ICE, given that it failed. Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to complete ICE, given that ICE succeeded.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to abort ICE due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down). Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to complete ICE, given that it failed. Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to complete ICE, given that ICE succeeded.

FX_TAB_SWITCH_SPINNER_TYPE.description: Firefox: If the spinner interstitial displays during tab switching, record if the tab being switched to has been seen (content was visible) before. If not, record if the tab is 'old' (> 1000ms since creation) or 'new'.

JS_PRIVILEGED_PARSER_COMPILE_LAZY_AFTER_.description: Time elapsed between the moment a function is lazy-parsed (end of parsing of the ScriptSource) and the moment it is recompiled as non-lazy (start of compilation), in milliseconds, for privileged code.

JS_WEB_PARSER_COMPILE_LAZY_AFTER_MS.description: Time elapsed between the moment a function is lazy-parsed (end of parsing of the ScriptSource) and the moment it is recompiled as non-lazy (start of compilation), in milliseconds, for web code.

DEVTOOLS_DOM_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools DOM Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_DOM_TIME_ACTIVE_SECONDS.description: How long has the DOM inspector been active (seconds)

FEED_PROTOCOL_USAGE.description: Usage counts of feed protocols used to load a page. (1=feed, 2=feed:http, 3=feed:https, 4=feed:brokenScheme, 5=pcast, 6=pcast:http, 7=pcast:https, 8=pcast:brokenScheme)

FX_TAB_CLOSE_PERMIT_UNLOAD_TIME_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken to run permitUnload on a browser during tab close to see whether or not we're allowed to close the tab (ms).

FX_TAB_CLOSE_TIME_ANIM_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken from the point of closing a tab (with animation), to the browser element being removed from the DOM. (ms).

FX_TAB_CLOSE_TIME_NO_ANIM_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken from the point of closing a tab (without animation) to the browser element being removed from the DOM. (ms).

IMAGE_ANIMATED_DECODE_ON_DRAW_LATENCY.description: Time from starting a decode of an animated image to it showing up on the screen (us)

IMAGE_ANIMATED_DECODE_TIME.description: Time spent decoding an animated image (us)

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_MAX_CONTIGUOUS_DROP.description: For APZ/scrolling compositor animations, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered
For compositor animations of chrome-process layers, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered
For compositor animations of content-process layers, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_APZ.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for APZ/scrolling animations in the compositor.

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_CHROME.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for compositor animations of chrome-process layers.

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_CONTENT.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for compositor animations of content-process layers.

HTTP_ONSTART_SUSPEND_TOTAL_TIME.description: Time in milliseconds that http channel spent suspended between AsyncOpen and OnStartRequest.

FX_PREFERENCES_CATEGORY_OPENED_V2.description: Count how often each preference category is opened.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled mouse move event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_TOUCH_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled touch move event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_WHEEL_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled wheel event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_CLICK_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse click event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_KEYBOARD_MS.description: Time (ms) for the keyboard event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_FRAME_.description: The number of pixels of the frame for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_PERCEN.description: The ratio of the frame size (in total number of pixels) to the relative limit (~viewport size plus some tolerance factor, typically 12.5% in each dimension, i.e. ~27% tolerance in total area) for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor expressed as a percentage (e.g. 130 = frame area was 30% larger than the relative limit)

DISPLAY_ITEM_USAGE_COUNT.description: Count of which layout display items are being created. Display items are created by layout to determine what content to render. A full description is above the class definition for nsDisplayItem. The list of types is kept in nsDisplayItemTypes.h.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_DISMISSED.description: Update: the dismiss action was executed for this application update doorhanger type.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_MAIN_ACTION_DOORHANG.description: Update: the main update action was initiated for this application update doorhanger type.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_MAIN_ACTION_MENU.description: Update: the update action was initiated from the PanelUI application update menu item.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_SHOWN.description: Update: the application update doorhanger type that was displayed.

URLCLASSIFIER_MATCH_THREAT_TYPE_RESULT.description: Whether or not a full URL match is of the same threat type on V2 and V4. (0 = same, otherwise the value is a bit flag where 0x01 = V2 phishing, 0x02 = V2 malware, 0x04 = V2 unwanted, 0x08 = V4 phishing, 0x10 = V4 malware, 0x20 = V4 unwanted)

FX_SEARCHBAR_SELECTED_RESULT_METHOD.description: The input method the user used to select a result in the searchbar. 'enter' => The user hit the Enter key without choosing a result in the popup. 'enterSelection' => The user chose a result and then hit the Enter key. 'click' => The user clicked a result with the mouse.

FX_URLBAR_SELECTED_RESULT_METHOD.description: The input method the user used to select a result in the urlbar. 'enter' => The user hit the Enter key on the heuristic result at index 0. 'enterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result (in exotic ways) and then hit the Enter key. 'click' => The user clicked a result with the mouse. 'arrowEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using arrow keys and then hit the Enter key. 'tabEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using tab at least once and then hit the Enter key. 'rightClickEnter' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using right click and then hit the Enter key.

GPU_PROCESS_CRASH_FALLBACKS.description: Count how often we use different fallbacks when the GPU process crashes: None=0, GPUProcessDecodingDisabled=1, GPUProcessDisabled=2

TIME_TO_DOM_COMPLETE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domComplete.

TIME_TO_DOM_CONTENT_LOADED_END_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domContentLoadedEventEnd.

TIME_TO_DOM_CONTENT_LOADED_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domContentLoadedEventStart.

TIME_TO_DOM_INTERACTIVE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domInteractive.

TIME_TO_DOM_LOADING_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domLoading.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_END_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to loadEventEnd.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to loadEventStart.

TIME_TO_RESPONSE_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to responseStart.

FORM_ISINDEX_USED.description: Whether there has been an isindex form submission in this session.

DISPLAY_SCALING.description: Scaling percentage for the display where the first window is opened

BOX_ALIGN_PROPS_IN_BLOCKS_FLAG.description: Whether we have layed out any display:block containers with not-yet-supported properties from CSS Box Align.

INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_COALESCED_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled, but with overlapping events coalesced.

MEDIA_EME_SECURE_CONTEXT.description: Reports whether a navigator.requestMediaKeySystemAccess() was called in a secure context (i.e. on an origin served over HTTPS) or not.

APZ_AWARE_KEY_LISTENERS.description: The percentage of pages with a non-passive key event on the path to the root scrolling element that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.

APZ_AWARE_MOUSEMOVE_LISTENERS.description: The percentage of pages with a mousemove listener anywhere in the document that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.

FX_SESSION_RESTORE_PRIVACY_LEVEL.description: Session restore: The privacy level chosen by the user (0: Collect data from all sites, 1: Collect data only from non-HTTPS sites, 2: Collect no data)

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_USAGE.description: Whether we raced network with the cache. (0=network & no racing, 1=cache & no racing, 2=network & raced, 3=cache & raced, 4=network & delayed race, 5=cache & delayed race)

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled mouse move event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_TOUCH_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled touch move event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_WHEEL_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled wheel event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_KEYBOARD_MS.description: Time (ms) for the keyboard event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_MOUSE_DOWN_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse down event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_MOUSE_UP_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse up event spent in handlers.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_BG_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the background and the script is not on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_BG_TRACKING_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the background and the script is on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_FG_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the foreground and the script is not on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_FG_TRACKING_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the foreground and the script is on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

CONTENT_JS_BACKGROUND_TICK_DELAY_TOTAL_M.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is completely in the background. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

CONTENT_JS_FOREGROUND_TICK_DELAY_TOTAL_M.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is (partially) in the foreground. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

CONTENT_JS_KNOWN_TICK_DELAY_MS.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup when the vsync event's timestamp is before the starting time of the runnable. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

TCP_FAST_OPEN.description: When a http connection is closed, track whether or not TCP Fast Open was used: 0=TFO_NOT_TRIED, 1=TFO_TRIED_NEGOTIATING, 2=TFO_DATA_SENT, 3=TFO_FAILED.

HTTP_AUTH_DIALOG_STATS_2.description: Stats about what kind of resource requested http authentication. (29=top-level doc, 30=same origin subresources, 31=same origin xhr, (nsIContentPolicy type)=cross-origin subresources per nsIContentPolicy type)

IPC_MESSAGE_SIZE2.description: Measures the size of all IPC messages sent that are >= 4096 bytes.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_FRAME_SIZE.description: The number of pixels of the frame each time we potentially run a transform animation on the compositor. Intended for comparison with ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_FRAME_SIZE.

FX_PREFERENCES_OPENED_VIA.description: Count how the Preferences are opened.

URLCLASSIFIER_VLPS_LONG_PREFIXES.description: Length of the first 20 long prefixes (> 4 bytes) received in a Safe Browsing V4 table during an update.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_OCEC_ON_.description: Time in milliseconds between onStartRequest from the cache and onCacheEntryCheck. Report only when net wins and OCEC is before onStartRequest from net.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_SAVED_TI.description: Time in milliseconds that we saved when we race cache with network.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWITH_NOT_RACE.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide not to race cache with network.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWITH_RACE_CACHE_W.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide to race cache with network and cache wins.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWITH_RACE_NETWORK.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide to race cache with network and network wins.

MEDIACACHE_BLOCKOWNERS_WATERMARK.description: Maximum number of owners for each MediaCache block. Recorded at every MediaCache destruction, i.e., whenever there is no more media data to be downloaded or kept for playback.

MEDIACACHE_WATERMARK_KB.description: Maximum MediaCache buffer size reached, in KB. Recorded at every MediaCache destruction, i.e., whenever there is no more media data to be downloaded or kept for playback.

VFC_CLEARCURRENTFRAME_LOCK_HOLD_MS.description: Time (ms) VideoFrameContainer::ClearCurrentFrame spent holding a lock.

VFC_CLEARFUTUREFRAMES_LOCK_HOLD_MS.description: Time (ms) VideoFrameContainer::ClearFutureFrames spent holding a lock.

VFC_INVALIDATE_LOCK_HOLD_MS.description: Time (ms) VideoFrameContainer::InvalidateWithFlags spent holding a lock.

VFC_INVALIDATE_LOCK_WAIT_MS.description: Time (ms) VideoFrameContainer::InvalidateWithFlags spent waiting for a lock.

VFC_SETCURRENTFRAME_LOCK_HOLD_MS.description: Time (ms) VideoFrameContainer::SetCurrentFrame spent holding a lock.

VIDEO_CHROMIUM_CDM_MAX_SHMEMS.description: Counts of the maximum number of shared memory buffers used for transferring video frames between the CDM and Gecko processes during playback of DRM'd video. Reported once per CDMVideoDecoder instance, i.e., once per JavaScript SourceBuffer during playback of video using EME.

GC_MAX_PAUSE_MS_2.description: Longest GC slice in a GC (ms)

GC_SLOW_TASK.description: The longest parallel task in any slice that goes over 2x the budget. The phase values are defined in js/src/gc/GenerateStatsPhases.py.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWIDTH_NOT_RACE.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide not to race cache with network.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWIDTH_RACE_CACHE_.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide to race cache with network and cache wins.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWIDTH_RACE_NETWOR.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide to race cache with network and network wins.

WEBEXT_BACKGROUND_PAGE_LOAD_MS.description: The amount of time it takes to load a WebExtensions background page, from when the build function is called to when the page has finished processing the onload event.

MEDIA_EME_REQUEST_DEPRECATED_WARNINGS.description: Counts types of deprecation warnings logged on every successful call to navigator.requestMediaKeySystemAccess(). 0=No warnings logged, 1=MediaEMENoCapabilitiesDeprecatedWarning, 2=MediaEMENoCodecsDeprecatedWarning.

PLUGINS_INFOBAR_DISMISSED.description: Count the number of times the user explicitly dismisses the hidden-plugin infobar without choosing allow or continue-blocking.

TELEMETRY_ARCHIVE_LOAD_MS.description: Time (ms) it takes for loading archived pings from disk

TELEMETRY_PENDING_LOAD_MS.description: Time (ms) it takes for loading pending pings from disk

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_BADGE_SHOWN.description: Update: the application update badge type that was displayed.

WEBEXT_EXTENSION_STARTUP_MS.description: The amount of time it takes for a WebExtension to start up, from when the startup function is called to when the startup promise resolves.

DOCUMENT_DATA_URI_LOADS.description: Whether a toplevel document uses data: URI? (0=data-navigated, 1=data-typed, 2=nodata)

TELEMETRY_SEND_FAILURE_TYPE.description: Counts of the different ways sending a Telemetry ping can fail.

WEBCRYPTO_METHOD_SECURE.description: Whether a method invoked under window.crypto.subtle is in a secure context

MEDIACACHESTREAM_LENGTH_KB.description: MediaCacheStream stream length size in KB; Either known size from the HTTP header if available, or otherwise the size actually downloaded. Recorded at every MediaCacheStream destruction.

TELEMETRY_FAILED_SEND_PINGS_SIZE_KB.description: The size (KB) of the Telemetry unsuccessfully sent pings

TELEMETRY_SUCCESSFUL_SEND_PINGS_SIZE_KB.description: The size (KB) of the Telemetry successfully sent pings

MEDIACACHESTREAM_NOTIFIED_LENGTH.description: MediaCacheStream stream notified length size in bytes, from the HTTP header. Recorded when each MediaCacheStream is first notified.

SANDBOX_FAILED_LAUNCH.description: Error code when a Windows sandboxed process fails to launch. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/search?q=ResultCode++path%3Asandbox_types.h&redirect=true for definitions of the error codes.

MIXED_CONTENT_HSTS_PRIMING_2.description: How often would blocked mixed content be allowed if HSTS upgrades were allowed, including how often would we send an HSTS priming request? 0=passive/HSTS, 1=active/HSTS, 2=passive/no priming, 3=passive/priming, 4=active/no priming, 5=active/priming, 6=passive/will HSTS upgrade, 7=active/will HSTS upgrade

MIXED_CONTENT_HSTS_PRIMING_REQUESTS.description: How often does a request result in HSTS priming? (0=Sent HSTS priming, 1=No priming, 2=Priming skipped due to cached HSTS, 3=Priming skipped due to cached NO HSTS, 4=Priming failed (request error), 5=Priming skipped (missing load info), 6=Priming skipped (already upgraded)

CYCLE_COLLECTOR_SLICE_DURING_IDLE.description: Percent of cycle collector slice done during idle time

FORGET_SKIPPABLE_DURING_IDLE.description: Percent of the cycle collector's forget skippable done during idle time

GC_SLICE_DURING_IDLE.description: Percent of GC slice done during idle time

MEMORYBLOCKCACHE_ERRORS.description: Unexpected errors encountered during use of MemoryBlockCache. 0=InitUnderuse, 1=InitAllocation, 2=ReadOverrun, 3=WriteBlockOverflow, 4=WriteBlockCannotGrow, 5=MoveBlockSourceOverrun, 6=MoveBlockDestOverflow, 7=MoveBlockCannotGrow

HSTS_UPGRADE_SOURCE.description: When we record an upgrade due to HSTS, record the source of that HSTS entry. (0: HSTS preload list, 1: HSTS Header seen naturally, 2: HSTS priming)

WEBEXT_BROWSERACTION_POPUP_OPEN_MS.description: The amount of time it takes for a BrowserAction popup to open.

WEBEXT_BROWSERACTION_POPUP_PRELOAD_RESUL.description: The number of times a browserAction popup is preloaded and results in one of the categories.

WEBEXT_PAGEACTION_POPUP_OPEN_MS.description: The amount of time it takes for a PageAction popup to open.

DEVTOOLS_NUMBER_OF_CSS_GRIDS_IN_A_PAGE.description: On page load, record the number of CSS Grid elements present on a page when the DevTools is open

WEBEXT_CONTENT_SCRIPT_INJECTION_MS.description: The amount of time it takes for content scripts from a WebExtension to be injected into a window.

MEDIACACHE_MEMORY_WATERMARK.description: Maximum memory-backed-MediaCache memory usage reached, in bytes. Recorded at every Firefox shutdown if memory-backed-MediaCache was used.

PLACES_DATABASE_CORRUPTION_HANDLING_STAG.description: PLACES: stage reached when trying to fix a database corruption , see Places::Database::eCorruptDBReplaceStatus

WEBEXT_STORAGE_LOCAL_GET_MS.description: The amount of time it takes to perform a get via storage.local using the JSONFile backend.

WEBEXT_STORAGE_LOCAL_SET_MS.description: The amount of time it takes to perform a set via storage.local using the JSONFile backend.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_USAGE_2.description: Whether we raced network with the cache.

GC_BUDGET_OVERRUN.description: How long a GC slice ran over its budget in microseconds

HTTP_PAGE_TCP_CONNECTION_2.description: HTTP page channel: TCP SYN to Ready for HTTP (ms)

HTTP_PAGE_TLS_HANDSHAKE.description: HTTP page channel: After TCP SYN to Ready for HTTP (ms)

HTTP_SUB_TCP_CONNECTION_2.description: HTTP subitem channel: TCP SYN to Ready for HTTP (ms)

HTTP_SUB_TLS_HANDSHAKE.description: HTTP subitem channel: After TCP SYN to Ready for HTTP (ms)

IMAGE_REQUEST_DISPATCHED.description: Track how many image requests required event dispatching because we were unable to predict the correct scheduler group: true if the request required dispatching. See image/imgRequestProxy.cpp for details.

HOVER_UNTIL_UNSELECTED_TAB_OPENED.description: Measure the time how long the cursor is hovering before opening the unselcted tab. Only record the data if someone requests for sending unselected tab hover msg.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_VALIDATION.description: Stats for validation requests when cache won the race.

WEBVR_TIME_SPEND_FOR_VIEWING_IN_2D.description: The amount of time spend(ms) for users who view VR content in 2D.

WEBVR_TIME_SPEND_FOR_VIEWING_IN_OCULUS.description: The amount of time spend(ms) for users who view VR content in Oculus.

WEBVR_TIME_SPEND_FOR_VIEWING_IN_OPENVR.description: The amount of time spend(ms) for users who view VR content in OpenVR.

WEBVR_USERS_VIEW_IN.description: The amount of sessions who view VR content in: 2D=0, Oculus=1, OpenVR=2.

DEVTOOLS_ENTRY_POINT.description: Records how the user is triggering Developer Tools startup.

FONTLIST_INITOTHERFAMILYNAMES_NO_DEFERRI.description: Time(ms) spent on reading other family names from all fonts for no timeout case

URLCLASSIFIER_UI_EVENTS.description: URL CLassifier-related (aka Safe Browsing) UI events. See nsIUrlClassifierUITelemetry.idl for the specific values.

WEBAUTHN_CREATE_CREDENTIAL_MS.description: Time in milliseconds to complete a WebAuthn create credential.

WEBAUTHN_GET_ASSERTION_MS.description: Time in milliseconds to complete a WebAuthn get assertion.

WEBVR_TIME_SPENT_VIEWING_IN_2D.description: The amount of time spent(ms) of a session for viewing VR content in 2D.

WEBVR_TIME_SPENT_VIEWING_IN_OCULUS.description: The amount of time spent(ms) of a session for viewing content in Oculus.

WEBVR_TIME_SPENT_VIEWING_IN_OPENVR.description: The amount of time spent(ms) of a session for viewing content in OpenVR.

USE_COUNTER2_DOMERRORCONSTRUCTOR_DOCUMEN.description: Whether a document constructed a DOMError

USE_COUNTER2_DOMERRORCONSTRUCTOR_PAGE.description: Whether a page constructed a DOMError

TAB_COUNT.description: Number of tabs opened across all windows, collected at most every 5 minutes whenever the user interacts with the browser in the following ways: open tab/window, page load.

TCP_FAST_OPEN_2.description: When a http connection is closed, track whether or not TCP Fast Open was used: 0=TFO_NOT_TRIED(There was no http connection and it was not TLS), 1=TFO_TRIED_NEGOTIATING, 2=TFO_DATA_SENT, 3=TFO_FAILED_CONNECTION_REFUSED, 4=TFO_FAILED_NET_TIMEOUT, 5=TFO_FAILED_UNKNOW_ERROR, 6=TFO_FAILED_BACKUP_CONNECTION, 7=TFO_FAILED_CONNECTION_REFUSED_NO_TFO_FAILED_TOO, 8=TFO_FAILED_NET_TIMEOUT__NO_TFO_FAILED_TOO, 9=TFO_FAILED_UNKNOW_ERROR_NO_TFO_FAILED_TOO, 10=TFO_FAILED_BACKUP_CONNECTION_NO_TFO_FAILED_TOO.

TCP_FAST_OPEN_STATUS.description: TCP Fast Open was: 0=enabled during the session, 1=not available or disabled in the os, 2=disabled by the pref, 3=disabled based on the too many connection failures, 4=disable based on too many http transaction stalls after a connection was idle.

SERVICE_WORKER_LAUNCH_TIME.description: Time (ms) for a service worker to start up.

FX_TAB_SWITCH_REQUEST_TAB_WARMING_STATE.description: Firefox: When a tab is selected, records whether or not the tab was speculatively 'warmed up' to improve tab switch time.

INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_POST_STARTUP_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled, but with overlapping events coalesced, which happens after the process is ready for interaction.

INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_STARTUP_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled, but with overlapping events coalesced, which happens before the process is ready for interaction.

WEAVE_LOGIN_FAILED_FOR.description: The number of minutes the user was in a bad login state.

WEBVR_DROPPED_FRAMES_IN_OCULUS.description: The average number of dropped frames per sec in Oculus, sent when user exits WebVR content.

WEBVR_DROPPED_FRAMES_IN_OPENVR.description: The average number of dropped frames per sec in OpenVR, sent when user exits WebVR content.

WEBRTC_RTCP_MUX.description: Was RTCP-MUX negotiated for a track

PAGE_METADATA_SIZE.description: The size of the description and preview image url for page metadata (Bytes)

URLCLASSIFIER_THREATHIT_NETWORK_ERROR.description: Whether or not an error was encountered while sending a Safe Browsing ThreatHit report. (0=sucess, 1=unknown error, 2=already connected, 3=not connected, 4=connection refused,5=net timeout, 6=offline, 7=port access not allowed, 8=net reset, 9=net interrupt, 10=proxy connection refused, 11=partial transfer, 12=inadequate security, 13=unknown host, 14=dns lookup queue full, 15=unknown proxy host)

URLCLASSIFIER_THREATHIT_REMOTE_STATUS.description: Server HTTP status code from Safe Browsing ThreatHit report. (0=1xx, 1=200, 2=2xx, 3=204, 4=3xx, 5=400, 6=4xx, 7=403, 8=404, 9=408, 10=413, 11=5xx, 12=502|504|511, 13=503, 14=505, 15=Other)

FX_PAGE_ACTION_ADDED.description: Count how many times people add items to the url bar

FX_PAGE_ACTION_PANEL_USED.description: Count how many times people use items from the main page action button

FX_PAGE_ACTION_REMOVED.description: Count how many times people remove items from the url bar

FX_PAGE_ACTION_URLBAR_USED.description: Count how many times people use items in the url bar

MEDIA_RECORDER_RECORDING_DURATION.description: The length of time (in seconds) that a recording lasted. Recorded when a recorder stops

MEDIA_RECORDER_TRACK_ENCODER_INIT_TIMEOU.description: Records the type of timeout that happened while attempting to init the encoder. Audio = 0, Video = 1. Recorded immediately following a timeout

MEDIA_ANDROID_VIDEO_TUNNELING_SUPPORT.description: Records whether tunneled playback is supported by a video decoder when creating it.

COOKIE_SCHEME_HTTPS.description: How often are first- and third-party cookies set from HTTPS origins? 0=first/http, 1=first/http+secure?!, 2=first/https, 3=first/https+secure, 4=third/http, 5=third/http+secure?!, 6=third/https, 7=third/https+secure

PREDICTOR_PREFETCH_DECISION_REASON.description: Why the predictor determined a particular resource was eligible for future prefetch (or not). See PrefetchDecisionReason in Predictor.cpp for value meanings

PREDICTOR_PREFETCH_IGNORE_REASON.description: Why the predictor determined a particular resource that was marked eligible for prefetch should not be prefetched. See PrefetchIgnoreReason in Predictor.cpp for value meanings

MOZ_SQLITE_COOKIES_BLOCK_MAIN_THREAD_MS.description: Time spent on blocking main thread by startup cookie database read (ms)

DEVTOOLS_INSPECTOR_NEW_ROOT_TO_RELOAD_DE.description: Time taken (in ms) to update the inspector during a page reload, starting from new-root event.

FX_SCHEDULE_PRESSURE_IDLE_SAMPLE_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken to get an idle callback while loading a page (ms). Loading of about: pages is not counted.

PLUGINS_NOTIFICATION_USER_ACTION_2.description: User actions taken in the plugin notification: 0: allownow 1: allowalways 2: block 3: blockalways; Note: 1 and 3 are unused from Firefox 69 onwards.

MOZ_SQLITE_COOKIES_OLD_SCHEMA.description: Old schema version of the cookie database. 0 for having legacy cookies.txt.

DEVTOOLS_ABOUT_DEVTOOLS_OPENED_KEY.description: Records the key shortcut passed to open the about:devtools page.

DEVTOOLS_ABOUT_DEVTOOLS_OPENED_REASON.description: Records the reason for opening the about:devtools page.

FX_PAGE_ACTION_MANAGED.description: Count how many times people manage extensions via their actions in the url bar

MOZ_SQLITE_COOKIES_BLOCK_MAIN_THREAD_MS_.description: Time spent on blocking main thread by startup cookie database read (ms), only for blocking case

MOZ_SQLITE_COOKIES_TIME_TO_BLOCK_MAIN_TH.description: How long (ms) after we finished reading the cookie db until the first cookie request came in (0 implies we blocked the main thread)

SCRIPT_LOADED_WITH_VERSION.description: Tracking how often scripts are loaded with a 'valid' version parameter. This telemetry ID helps us to decide if and when remove the support of script versioning.

TIME_TO_NON_BLANK_PAINT_NETOPT_MS.description: The time between navigation start and the first non-blank paint of a foreground root content document, in milliseconds. This only records documents that were in an active docshell throughout the whole time between navigation start and non-blank paint. The non-blank paint timestamp is taken during display list building and does not include rasterization or compositing of that paint.  This probe only accumulates when there were active-tab network load optimizations happening during the interval.

TIME_TO_NON_BLANK_PAINT_NO_NETOPT_MS.description: The time between navigation start and the first non-blank paint of a foreground root content document, in milliseconds. This only records documents that were in an active docshell throughout the whole time between navigation start and non-blank paint. The non-blank paint timestamp is taken during display list building and does not include rasterization or compositing of that paint.  This probe only accumulates when there were no active-tab network load optimizations happening during the interval.

USER_CHROME_CSS_LOADED.description: Was a userChrome.css stylesheet loaded when the profile was initialized?

A11Y_UIA_DETECTION_TIMING_MS.description: The amount of time the parent process blocked while detecting a UIA client.

HTTP_AUTH_DIALOG_STATS_3.description: Stats about what kind of resource requested http authentication. (29=top-level doc, 30=same origin subresources, 31=same origin xhr, 32=non-web-content, (nsIContentPolicy type)=cross-origin subresources per nsIContentPolicy type)

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 20 <= N <= 24, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 25 <= N <= 29, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 2 <= N <= 4, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 30 <= N <= 34, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 35 <= N <= 39, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 40 <= N <= 44, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

When a document is loaded, if the user has a number of loaded tabs in the range 45 <= N <= 49, report the ratio of unique site origins loaded to number of loaded tabs (multiplied by 100) if it has been at least 5 minutes since the last collection

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_END_NO_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time from navigationStart to loadEventEnd as per the W3C Performance Timing API. This is only submitted on when the document would not preload a resource.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_END_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time from navigationStart to loadEventEnd as per the W3C Performance Timing API. This is submitted only when the document would preload a resource (i.e., if it encounters a <link> element or a Link with rel="preload"), even if the network.preload pref is disabled.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_START_NO_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time from navigationStart to loadEventStart as per the W3C Performance Timing API. This is only submitted on when the document would not preload a resource.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_START_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time from navigationStart to loadEventStart as per the W3C Performance Timing API. This is submitted only when the document would preload a resource (i.e., if it encounters a <link> element or a Link header with rel="preload"), even if the network.preload pref is disabled.

LOAD_INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_NO_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled for events handled during page load only. This is only submitted on when the document would not preload a resource.

LOAD_INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled for events handled during page load only. This is submitted only when the document would preload a resource (i.e., if it encounters a <link> element or a Link header with rel="preload"), even if the network.preload pref is disabled.

TIME_TO_FIRST_INTERACTION_NO_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click, key, mouse or scroll event per top-level content browsing context. This is only submitted on when the document would not preload a resource.

TIME_TO_FIRST_INTERACTION_PRELOAD_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click, key, mouse or scroll event per top-level content browsing context. This is submitted only when the document would preload a resource (i.e., if it encounters a <link> element or a Link header with rel="preload"), even if the network.preload pref is disabled.

PRINT_INIT_TO_PLATFORM_SENT_SETTINGS_MS.description: Milliseconds taken from when a print is initiated (typically by the user) to when the platform code is sent the print settings to create the initial print preview document.

PRINT_INIT_TO_PREVIEW_DOC_SHOWN_MS.description: Milliseconds taken from when a print is initiated (typically by the user) to when the initial print preview document is shown.

USE_COUNTER2_CSS_PROPERTY_MathStyle_PAGE.description: Whether a page used the CSS property math-style

HTTP3_BLOCKED_BY_STREAM_LIMIT_PER_CONN.description: HTTP3: number of times a connection is blocked by maximum allowed number of parallel streams per connection

HTTP3_SENDING_BLOCKED_BY_FLOW_CONTROL_PE.description: HTTP3: number of times when a stream is blocked by the flow control while sendnig data.

HTTP3_TIMER_DELAYED.description: Time difference between setting timer value and actually firing the timer for calling neqo

HTTP3_TRANS_BLOCKED_BY_STREAM_LIMIT_PER_.description: HTTP3: number of transactions that are blocked by maximum allowed number of parallel streams per connection

HTTP3_TRANS_SENDING_BLOCKED_BY_FLOW_CONT.description: HTTP3: number of times streams are blocked by the flow control while sending data per connection

previousBuildId.description: null if this is the first run, or the previous build ID is unknown

previousSessionId.description: session id of the previous session, null on first run.

previousSubsessionId.description: subsession id of the previous subsession (even if it was in a different session), null on first run.

profileSubsessionCounter.description: the running no. of all subsessions for the whole profile life time

reason.description: what triggered this ping e.g. saved-session, environment-change, shutdown, ...

sessionId.description: random session id, shared by subsessions

sessionLength.description: the session length until now in seconds, monotonic; some clients report erroneous negative values

sessionStartDate.description: hourly precision, ISO date in local time

subsessionCounter.description: the running no. of this subsession since the start of the browser session

subsessionLength.description: the subsession length until now in seconds, monotonic

subsessionStartDate.description: hourly precision, ISO date in local time

timezoneOffset.description: time-zone offset from UTC, in minutes, for the current locale

additionalProperties.description: Time (ms) that the main thread has been blocked on PluginAsyncSurrogate::WaitForInit in an IPC plugin
Time (ms) that the main thread has been blocked on NPP_Destroy in an IPC plugin
Time (ms) that the main thread has been blocked on NPP_New in an IPC plugin

Time (ms) that the main thread has been blocked on NPP_NewStream in an IPC plugin
Exceptions thrown by add-ons

Records search counts for search access points and in-content searches. For search access points in general, the format is: <engine-name>.<search-access-point> For the urlbar when in search mode, the format is <engine name>.urlbar-searchmode For the urlbar when an internal @engine shortcut is used, the format is: <engine-name>.alias For in-content searches, the format is <provider>.in-content:[sap|sap-follow-on|organic]:[code|none]
Counts of plugin/content process abnormal shutdown, whether or not a crash report was available.
Counts of plugin and content process crashes which are reported with a crash dump.
Reports the column that logins are sorted by
Update: keyed count (key names are prefixed with AUS_CHECK_EX_ERR_) of background update check extended error code (externally initiated)
Update: keyed count (key names are prefixed with AUS_CHECK_EX_ERR_) of background update check extended error code (timer initiated)
Reasons why add-on shims were used, keyed by add-on ID.
When a user starts a recording with specific recording options, keyed by feature name (withMarkers, withAllocations, etc.).
The amount of time spent in a specific performance tool view, keyed by view name (waterfall, js-calltree, js-flamegraph, etc).
What runtime app type did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime ID did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime OS did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime platform version did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime processor did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime type did WebIDE connect to?
What runtime version did WebIDE connect to?
An attempt to submit a crash. Keyed on the CrashManager Crash.type.
The submission status when main/plugin/content crashes are submitted. 1 is success, 0 is failure. Keyed on the CrashManager Crash.type.
Count of individual invalid ping types that were submitted to Telemetry.
A number of sucessfully translated pages by language
A number of successful and failed attempts to translate a document grouped by language
Exceptions thrown by a Sync engine. Keyed on the engine name.
Errors encountered during migration in buckets defined by the datatype, keyed by the string description of the browser.
Usage of migration for each datatype when migration is run through the post-firstrun flow which allows individual datatypes, keyed by the string description of the browser.
Number of toplevel location changes in tablet and desktop mode (only used on win10 where tablet mode is available)
(Bug 1207089) Time in ms between displaying a popup notification and dismissing it without an action the first time, keyed by ID
(Bug 1207089) Time in ms between initially requesting a popup notification and triggering the main action, keyed by ID

(Bug 1207089) Usage of popup notifications, keyed by ID (0 = Offered, 1..4 = Action (3 is unused), 5 = Click outside (unused), 6 = Leave page, 7 = Use 'X' (unused), 8 = Not now (unused), 10 = Open submenu, 11 = Learn more. Add 20 if happened after reopen.)

Count of use of audio/video codecs in HTMLMediaElements and WebAudio. Those with 'resource' prefix are approximate; report based on HTTP ContentType or sniffing. Those with 'webaudio' prefix are for WebAudio.
The number of times a given type of breakdown was used for a census
The number of times a given type of breakdown was used for a dominator tree
Records the key-identifiers of error messages when they are displayed in the webconsole of the debugger. Nothing should be recorded unless they are visible on the user screen.
Measures the size of IPC messages by message name
Tracking how long a Worker thread is blocked when a sync operation is executed on the main-thread.
Counts the number of times a subprocess was forcibly killed, and the reason.

WebGL runtime and dynamic failure IDs. This will record a count for each context creation success or failure. Each failure id is a unique identifier that can be traced back to a particular failure branch or blocklist rule.
Track the failure IDs that lead us to reject attempting to create an accelerated context. CANVAS_WEBGL_FAILURE_ID reports the overall WebGL status with the attempt to fallback.
Counts the number of times launching a subprocess fails. Counts are by subprocess-type using the GeckoProcessType enum.
Each key is the message name, with digits removed, from an async message manager message that was rejected for being over approximately 128MB, recorded in the sending process at the time of sending.

Counts of various Decoder Doctor notification events. Used to track efficacy of Decoder Doctor at helping users fix problems with their audio/video codecs. Keys are localized string names that identify problem with audio/video codecs that Decoder Doctor attempts to solve; see string values in dom.properties for verbose description of problems being solved. 0=recorded every time the Decoder Doctor notification is shown, 1=recorded the first time in a profile when notification is shown, 2=recorded when 'Learn how' button clicked, 3=recorded when 'Learn how' button first clicked in a profile, 4=recorded when issue solved after infobar has been shown at least once in a profile.

The 'last modified' time of the data we imported on the initial profile migration (time delta with 'now' at the time of migration, in hours). Collected for all browsers for which migration data is available, and stored keyed by browser identifier (e.g. 'ie', 'edge', 'safari', etc.).
Whether the browser we migrated from was the browser with the most recent data. Keyed by that browser's identifier (e.g. 'ie', 'edge', 'safari', etc.).
Counts the number of times a given add-on used CPOWs when it was marked as e10s compatible.

D3D11 compositor runtime and dynamic failure IDs. This will record a count for each context creation success or failure. Each failure id is a unique identifier that can be traced back to a particular failure branch or blocklist rule.

D3D9 compositor runtime and dynamic failure IDs. This will record a count for each context creation success or failure. Each failure id is a unique identifier that can be traced back to a particular failure branch or blocklist rule.

OpenGL compositor runtime and dynamic failure IDs. This will record a count for each context creation success or failure. Each failure id is a unique identifier that can be traced back to a particular failure branch or blocklist rule.

Percentage of total time spent playing video while element is hidden. Keyed by audio presence and by height ranges (boundaries: 240. 480, 576, 720, 1080, 2160), e.g.: 'V,0<h<=240', 'AV,h>2160'; and 'All' will accumulate all percentages. This is reported whenever an HTML Media Element is suspended or resumed, such as when the page is unloaded.
A counter incremented every time the user prints a document.

Average interval between video keyframes in played videos, in milliseconds. Keyed by audio presence and by height ranges (boundaries: 240. 480, 576, 720, 1080, 2160), e.g.: 'V,0<h<=240', 'AV,h>2160'; and 'All' will accumulate all percentages. This is reported whenever an HTML Media Element is suspended or resumed, such as when the page is unloaded.

Maximum interval between video keyframes in played videos, in milliseconds; '0' means only 1 keyframe found. Keyed by audio presence and by height ranges (boundaries: 240. 480, 576, 720, 1080, 2160), e.g.: 'V,0<h<=240', 'AV,h>2160'; and 'All' will accumulate all percentages. This is reported whenever an HTML Media Element is suspended or resumed, such as when the page is unloaded.

Percentage of total time spent *not* fully decoding video while element is hidden (simulated, even when feature is not enabled). Keyed by audio presence and by height ranges (boundaries: 240. 480, 576, 720, 1080, 2160), e.g.: 'V,0<h<=240', 'AV,h>2160'; and 'All' will accumulate all percentages. This is reported whenever an HTML Media Element is suspended or resumed, such as when the page is unloaded.

Time taken for a video to resume after decoding was suspended, in milliseconds. Keyed by audio presence, hw acceleration, and by height ranges (boundaries: 240. 480, 720, 1080, 2160), e.g.: 'V,0-240', 'AV(hw),2160+'; and 'All' will accumulate all percentages.
How long it took to import bookmarks from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser.
How long it took to import history from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser.
How long it took to import logins (passwords) from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser. The time for users to unlock Keychain on macOS is included in this time.

Why the undo functionality of an automatic migration was disabled: 0 means we used undo, 1 means the user signed in to sync, 2 means the user created/modified a password, 3 means the user created/modified a bookmark (item or folder), 4 means we showed an undo option repeatedly and the user did not use it, 5 means we showed an undo option and the user actively elected to keep the data. The whole thing is keyed to the identifiers of different browsers (so 'chrome', 'ie', 'edge', 'safari', etc.).
Whether the homepage was imported during browser migration. Only available on release builds during firstrun.

Number of revoke actions on permissions in the control center, keyed by permission id. Values represent the permission type that was revoked. (0=unknown, 1=permanently allowed, 2=permanently blocked, 3=temporarily allowed, 4=temporarily blocked)
A counter incremented every time the user opens print dialog.

Percentages of times for phases in an expensive content paint relative to the time spent in the entire expensive paint. ("dl" = Display list, "flb" = Frame layer builder, "fr" = Flush rasterization, "r" = Rasterization)
The amount of time required for HSTS priming requests (ms), keyed by success or failure of the priming request. (success, failure)
How many bookmarks we imported from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser.
How many history visits we imported from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser.
How many logins (passwords) we imported from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser.
Time spent per classifier update (ms), keyed by the name of the provider.

Whether or not an error was encountered while processing a Safe Browsing update (0 = success, 1 = unspecified error, 2 = addition of an already existing prefix, 3 = parser got into an infinite loop, 4 = removal index out of bounds, 5 = checksum mismatch, 6 = missing checksum, 7 = update while shutdown, 8 = cannot find table, 9 = build prefix failure, 10 = write disk failure, 11 = protocol parser error). Keyed by provider

Server HTTP status code from SafeBrowsing database updates. (0=1xx, 1=200, 2=2xx, 3=204, 4=3xx, 5=400, 6=4xx, 7=403, 8=404, 9=408, 10=413, 11=5xx, 12=502|504|511, 13=503, 14=505, 15=Other). Keyed by provider
Number of Narrate initialization attempts and successes broken up by content's language (ISO 639-1 code) (0 = initialization attempt, 1 = successfully initialized)

Server HTTP status code from remote SafeBrowsing gethash lookups. (0=1xx, 1=200, 2=2xx, 3=204, 4=3xx, 5=400, 6=4xx, 7=403, 8=404, 9=408, 10=413, 11=5xx, 12=502|504|511, 13=503, 14=505, 15=Other). Keyed by provider
This metric is recorded every time a gethash lookup is performed, `true` is recorded if the lookup times out. Keyed by provider
The time a given main thread runnable took to run (in milliseconds). The key comes from the runnables nsINamed::name value.
Indicates how many errors we find when trying to 'undo' bookmarks import. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how long it took to undo the startup import of bookmarks, in ms. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how many errors we find when trying to 'undo' login (password) import. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how long it took to undo the startup import of logins, in ms. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how long it took to undo the entirety of the startup undo, in ms. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how many errors we find when trying to 'undo' history import. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
Indicates how long it took to undo the startup import of visits (history), in ms. Keys are internal ids of browsers we import from, e.g. 'chrome' or 'ie', etc.
The amount of time the content process blocked processing shouldLoad shims for an add-on (keyed by add-on ID) after the load event, for each document load.
The amount of time the content process blocked processing shouldLoad shims for an add-on (keyed by add-on ID) prior to the load event, for each document load.

Accumulated timer delay (variance between when the timer was expected to fire and when it actually fired) in milliseconds as an indicator for decreased main-thread responsiveness while importing bookmarks from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser (see gAvailableMigratorKeys in MigrationUtils.jsm). The import is happening on a background thread and should ideally not affect the UI noticeably.

Accumulated timer delay (variance between when the timer was expected to fire and when it actually fired) in milliseconds as an indicator for decreased main-thread responsiveness while importing history from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser (see gAvailableMigratorKeys in MigrationUtils.jsm). The import is happening on a background thread and should ideally not affect the UI noticeably.

Accumulated timer delay (variance between when the timer was expected to fire and when it actually fired) in milliseconds as an indicator for decreased main-thread responsiveness while importing logins / passwords from another browser, keyed by the name of the browser (see gAvailableMigratorKeys in MigrationUtils.jsm). The import is happening on a background thread and should ideally not affect the UI noticeably. The time with the blocking Keychain dialog on macOS can skew this data.

System calls blocked by a seccomp-bpf sandbox policy; limited to syscalls where we would crash on Nightly.  The key is generally the architecture and syscall ID but in some cases we include non-personally-identifying information from the syscall arguments; see the function SubmitToTelemetry in security/sandbox/linux/reporter/SandboxReporter.cpp for details.
Track the size of results of get() operations performed this subsession. The key is the addon ID.
Track the number of remove() operations addons perform this subsession. The key is the addon ID.
Track the size of set() operations performed by addons this subsession. The key is the addon ID.

Network error from SafeBrowsing database updates. (0=sucess, 1=unknown error, 2=already connected, 3=not connected, 4=connection refused,5=net timeout, 6=offline, 7=port access not allowed, 8=net reset, 9=net interrupt, 10=proxy connection refused,11=partial transfer,12=inadequate security,13=unknown host,14=dns lookup queue full,15=unknown proxy host
Note the encoding (e.g. 'UTF-8', 'windows-1252', 'ASCII') of each external <script> element that is successfully loaded and decoded.

Measures the number of milliseconds we spend waiting for sync IPC messages to finish sending, keyed by message name. Note: only messages that wait for more than 500 microseconds and block the main thread are included in this probe.

Measures the number of milliseconds we spend waiting on the main thread for IPC messages to deserialize their parameters. Note: only messages that take more than 500 microseconds are included in this probe. This probe is keyed on the IPDL message name.

Measures the number of milliseconds we spend waiting on the main thread for IPC messages to serialize their parameters. Note: only messages that take more than 500 microseconds are included in this probe. This probe is keyed on the IPDL message name.

Measures the number of milliseconds we spend waiting for sync message manager IPC messages to finish sending, keyed by message name. Note: only messages that wait for more than 500 microseconds are included in this probe.
Server response time to getHash request (ms). Keyed by provider
Server response time to update request (ms). Keyed by provider
Reports the command name used in GCLI e.g. 'screenshot'

Absolute difference of each content process' USS and the mean of USS's, normalized by the mean, in percentage. It will be recorded with the rest of the memory probes when gatherMemory is called, if at least 2 content processes are alive. Example: in case of 4 content processes with USS's: 1G, 500MB, 1G, 1.5G, the reported numbers will be: 0, 50, 0, 50. Which indicates that 2 processes used 50% more or 50% less memory than the avarage and 2 used exactly as much as the avarage.

Firefox: The index of the selected result in the URL bar popup by the type of the selected result in the URL bar popup. See BrowserUsageTelemetry.jsm:URLBAR_SELECTED_RESULT_TYPES for the result types.

Time taken (in ms) from the point of the parent sending the naviagion triggering message to the content and the content receiving it. This message can be either SessionStore:restoreTabContent or WebNavigation:LoadURI and these names are used as keys for this histogram. This is e10s only and recorded in the content process.
Whether or not an update timed out (0 = no timeout, 1 = server respond timeout, 2 = overall timeout). Keyed by provider
Session restore: Duration of data collection in the content process (ms). Possible keys currently are: historychange, scroll, formdata, pageStyle, disallow, storage, storagechange.

Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is completely in the background. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution. The histogram is keyed by the label of the runnable, indicating which type of task the runnable is performing.

Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is (partially) in the foreground. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution. The histogram is keyed by the label of the runnable, indicating which type of task the runnable is performing.
Time (in ms) measured between when the fetch handler finished executing and when we reset the network channel.

Time (in ms) measured between when the fetch event is dispatched by the Service Worker and before we execute the event listeners. This effectively measures the SW backlong, in the future this should also cover the IPC steps required to dispatch events to the SW.
Time (in ms) measured between when the respondWith promise resolves and when we provide the response through the intercepted channel (FinishSynthesizedResponse).

Time delta (ms) between when a network request is intercepted and the service worker provides a response. This includes: possible SW startup, worker thread dispatch, time until the respondWith() promise resolves, time to synthesize the response (including the body), worker thread to main thread dispatch. In the future this should include the IPC roundtrips involved in fetch interception.

Measures the number of milliseconds we spend processing sync IPC messages in the receiving process, keyed by message name. Note: only messages that take over 500 microseconds are included in this probe.
Generic histogram to track uptake of remote content like blocklists, settings or updates.
The time a given runnable exceeds its budget as set in nsIRunnable::SetDeadline (in milliseconds). The key comes from the runnables nsINamed::name value.
Measures the number of milliseconds we spend synchronously notifying observers, keyed by topic. Note: only NotifyObservers calls which take over 500 microseconds are included in this probe.
Milliseconds between starting to fill an autofill-eligible form field and submitting the form, keyed by the combination of form type and filling type.

Error code when a Windows sandboxed process fails to launch, keyed by process type and Windows error code. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/search?q=ResultCode++path%3Asandbox_types.h&redirect=true for definitions of the error codes.
Time taken (in ms) to open the first DevTools toolbox. This is keyed by tool ID being opened [inspector, webconsole, jsdebugger, styleeditor, performance, memory, netmonitor, storage, dom].
Time taken (in ms) to open all but first DevTools toolbox. This is keyed by tool ID being opened [inspector, webconsole, jsdebugger, styleeditor, performance, memory, netmonitor, storage, dom].

Time taken (in ms) to update DevTools panel when reloading a page. This is keyed by tool ID being currently opened [inspector, webconsole, jsdebugger, styleeditor, performance, memory, netmonitor, storage, dom].
Count of the HTTP redirection that triggered by top-level document or by subresource, keyed by the URL scheme redirected to.
The number of prefs in each prefs file loaded, keyed by filename.
The size (in bytes) of each prefs file loaded, keyed by filename.
The time (in microseconds) to load, parse and process each prefs file, keyed by filename.
Permission requests (showing a permission prompt) by whether they were requested from code handling a user input event.
Permission requests (showing a permission prompt) by origin scheme (0=other,1=http,2=https).
Permission requests (showing a permission prompt) by whether they come from a third party origin.

Result of the content signature verification keyed by application (certificate fingerprint). 0=valid, 1=invalid, 2=noCertChain, 3=createContextFailedWithOtherError, 4=expiredCert, 5=certNotValidYet, 6=buildCertChainFailed, 7=eeCertForWrongHost, 8=extractKeyError, 9=vfyContextError
Upgrading display content Channel Disposition

ms of SSL wait time for full handshake including TCP and proxy tunneling, keyed by the key exchange algorithm used
Getting the number of errors in QuotaManager initialization.
Application reputation remote verdict, keyed by file extension
Counts of the different ways sending a Telemetry ping can fail per ping type.

Percentage increase of cache entry count that would be caused by first party isolation without deduplication keyed by content type.
Percentage increase of cache size that would be caused by first party isolation without deduplication keyed by content type.
Number of unique sites accessing the cache entry keyed by content type.

Numbers of HTTP transactions and connections by type. There are some categories separated by labels based on 4 parameters: 1. normal browsing or private browsing 2. first party or third party 3. class of service (Leader/Background/Others) 4. tracking classification (Basic/Content/FingerprintingContent).
Number of entries in the cache keyed by cache capacity calculation type. Numbers are sampled periodically, every time 2GB of data is written to the cache.
Percentage of the entries with the given content type. Numbers are sampled periodically, every time 2GB of data is written to the cache.
Cache size in megabytes keyed by cache capacity calculation type. Numbers are sampled periodically, every time 2GB of data is written to the cache.
Percentage of the cache size occupied by given content type. Numbers are sampled periodically, every time 2GB of data is written to the cache.

Numbers of HTTP transactions and connections by type. There are some categories separated by labels based on 5 parameters: 1. normal browsing or private browsing 2. system principal or not 3. first party or third party 4. class of service (Leader/Background/Others) 5. tracking classification (Basic/Content/FingerprintingContent).
How many milliseconds it took before 100 wakeups for the thread was done because of new Runnables.
Percentages of times for phases in an expensive refresh tick relative to the time spent in the entire tick (REFRESH_DRIVER_TICK).

True if the first initialization attempt succeeded, keyed by the initialization type.

lateWrites.description: This sections reports writes to the file system that happen during shutdown. The reported data contains the stack and the file names of the loaded libraries at the time the writes happened.

isFromTerminatorWatchdog.description: Bug 1634520 - 1 if the late writes began in nsTerminator, 0 otherwise

memoryMap.description: entries in the format [module name, breakpad identifier]

items.description: A list of stack frames, entries in the format [module index, program counter offset]. The module index can be -1 for invalid module indices. The program counter can be an offset in the module or an absolute pc.
