FX_SESSION_RESTORE_NUMBER_OF_EAGER_TABS_.description: Session restore: Number of tabs restored eagerly in the session that has just been restored.

FX_SESSION_RESTORE_NUMBER_OF_TABS_RESTOR.description: Session restore: Number of tabs in the session that has just been restored.

FX_SESSION_RESTORE_NUMBER_OF_WINDOWS_RES.description: Session restore: Number of windows in the session that has just been restored.

GEOLOCATION_REQUEST_GRANTED.description: Geolocation requests either granted or denied (0=denied/other, 1=denied/http, 2=denied/https, ..., 10=granted/other, 11=granted/http, 12=granted/https)

FENNEC_CUSTOM_HOMEPAGE.description: Whether the user has set a custom homepage.

MEDIA_RUST_MP4PARSE_ERROR_CODE.description: The error code reported when an MP4 parse attempt has failed.0 = OK, 1 = bad argument, 2 = invalid data, 3 = unsupported, 4 = unexpected end of file, 5 = read error.

CERT_CHAIN_SHA1_POLICY_STATUS.description: 1 = No SHA1 signatures, 2 = SHA1 certificates issued by an imported root, 3 = SHA1 certificates issued before 2016, 4 = SHA1 certificates issued after 2015, 5 = another error prevented successful verification

INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled

CHECKERBOARD_DURATION.description: Duration of a checkerboard event in milliseconds

CHECKERBOARD_PEAK.description: Peak number of CSS pixels checkerboarded during a checkerboard event (the high value is the size of a 4k display with max APZ zooming)

CHECKERBOARD_POTENTIAL_DURATION.description: Duration of a chunk of time (in ms) that could reasonably have had checkerboarding

CHECKERBOARD_SEVERITY.description: Opaque measure of the severity of a checkerboard event

E10S_STATUS.description: Why e10s is enabled or disabled (0=ENABLED_BY_USER, 1=ENABLED_BY_DEFAULT, 2=DISABLED_BY_USER, 3=DISABLED_IN_SAFE_MODE, 4=DISABLED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY, 5=DISABLED_FOR_MAC_GFX, 6=DISABLED_FOR_BIDI, 7=DISABLED_FOR_ADDONS, 8=FORCE_DISABLED, 9=DISABLED_FOR_XPLAYERS, 10=DISABLED_FOR_OS_VERSION)

AUDIO_MFT_OUTPUT_NULL_SAMPLES.description: How many times the audio MFT decoder returns success but output nothing.

VIDEO_MFT_OUTPUT_NULL_SAMPLES.description: Does the WMF video decoder return success but null output? 0 = playback successful, 1 = excessive null output but able to decode some frames, 2 = excessive null output and gave up, 3 = null output but recovered, 4 = non-excessive null output without being able to decode frames.

PLACES_MOST_RECENT_EXPIRED_VISIT_DAYS.description: PLACES: the most recent expired visit in days

FENNEC_BOOKMARKS_COUNT.description: Number of bookmarks stored in the browser DB

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_DIFF_CENSUS.description: Whether a census was the result of diffing or not

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_DOMINATOR_TREE_COUNT.description: The number of times a user requested a dominator tree be computed

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_EXPORT_SNAPSHOT_COUNT.description: The number of heap snapshots exported by a user

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_FILTER_CENSUS.description: Whether a census tree was filtered or not

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_IMPORT_SNAPSHOT_COUNT.description: The number of heap snapshots imported by a user

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_INVERTED_CENSUS.description: Whether a census tree was inverted or not

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_TAKE_SNAPSHOT_COUNT.description: The number of heap snapshots taken by a user

FENNEC_HOMEPANELS_CUSTOM.description: Whether the user has customized their homepanels

FENNEC_LOAD_SAVED_PAGE.description: How often users load saved items when online/offline (0=RL online, 1=RL offline, 2=BM online, 3=BM offline)

GC_COMPACT_MS.description: Time spent running JS GC compact phase (ms)

GFX_CONTENT_FAILED_TO_ACQUIRE_DEVICE.description: Failed to create a gfx content device. 0=content d3d11, 1=image d3d11, 2=d2d1.

SCROLL_INPUT_METHODS.description: Count of scroll actions triggered by different input methods. See gfx/layers/apz/util/ScrollInputMethods.h for a list of possible values and their meanings.

VIDEO_DROPPED_FRAMES_PROPORTION.description: Percentage of frames decoded frames dropped in an HTMLVideoElement

DEVTOOLS_ABOUTDEBUGGING_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times about:debugging has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_ANIMATIONINSPECTOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Animation Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_BROWSERCONSOLE_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Browser Console has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_CANVASDEBUGGER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Canvas Debugger has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_COMPUTEDVIEW_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Computed View has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_CUSTOM_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times a custom developer tool has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_DEVELOPERTOOLBAR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Developer Toolbar / GCLI has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_EYEDROPPER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Eyedropper tool has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_FONTINSPECTOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Font Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_INSPECTOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_JSBROWSERDEBUGGER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Browser Debugger has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_JSDEBUGGER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Debugger has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_JSPROFILER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools JS Profiler has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_LAYOUTVIEW_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Layout View has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_MEMORY_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Memory Tool has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_MENU_EYEDROPPER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Eyedropper has been opened via the DevTools menu.

DEVTOOLS_NETMONITOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Network Monitor has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_OPTIONS_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools options panel has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_PAINTFLASHING_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Paint Flashing has been opened via the toolbox button.

DEVTOOLS_PICKER_EYEDROPPER_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Eyedropper has been opened via the color picker.

DEVTOOLS_RESPONSIVE_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Responsive Design Mode tool has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_RULEVIEW_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Rule View has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_SCRATCHPAD_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Scratchpad toolbox panel has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_SCRATCHPAD_WINDOW_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Scratchpad standalone window has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_SHADEREDITOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Shader Editor has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_STORAGE_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Storage Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_STYLEEDITOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Style Editor has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_TILT_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Tilt has been opened via the toolbox button.

DEVTOOLS_TOOLBOX_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools toolbox has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_WEBAUDIOEDITOR_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Web Audio Editor has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_WEBCONSOLE_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools Web Console has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_WEBIDE_IMPORT_PROJECT_COUNT.description: Number of times a project has been imported into the DevTools WebIDE.

DEVTOOLS_WEBIDE_NEW_PROJECT_COUNT.description: Number of times a new project has been created in the DevTools WebIDE.

DEVTOOLS_WEBIDE_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools WebIDE has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_WEBIDE_PROJECT_EDITOR_OPENED_CO.description: Number of times the DevTools WebIDE project editor has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_WEBIDE_PROJECT_EDITOR_SAVE_COUN.description: Number of times a file has been saved in the DevTools WebIDE project editor.

BROWSER_SHIM_USAGE_BLOCKED.description: Counts the number of times a CPOW shim was blocked from being created by browser code.

MIXED_CONTENT_OBJECT_SUBREQUEST.description: How often objects load insecure content on secure pages (counting pages, not objects). 0=pages with no mixed object subrequests, 1=pages with mixed object subrequests

DEVTOOLS_RELOAD_ADDON_INSTALLED_COUNT.description: Number of times the reload addon has been installed.

DEVTOOLS_RELOAD_ADDON_RELOAD_COUNT.description: Number of times the tools have been reloaded by the reload addon.

SLOW_SCRIPT_PAGE_COUNT.description: The number of pages that trigger slow script notices

MEMORY_HEAP_OVERHEAD_FRACTION.description: Fraction of committed heap memory that is overhead (percentage).

VIDEO_VP9_BENCHMARK_FPS.description: 720p VP9 decode benchmark measurement in frames per second

CERT_EV_STATUS.description: EV status of a certificate, recorded on each TLS connection. 0=invalid, 1=DV, 2=EV

CSP_DOCUMENTS_COUNT.description: Number of unique pages that contain a CSP

CSP_UNSAFE_EVAL_DOCUMENTS_COUNT.description: Number of unique pages that contain an unsafe-eval CSP directive

CSP_UNSAFE_INLINE_DOCUMENTS_COUNT.description: Number of unique pages that contain an unsafe-inline CSP directive

PRCONNECT_FAIL_BLOCKING_TIME_CONNECTIVIT.description: Time spent blocked in a failed PR_Connect when there has been the connectiviy change in the last 60s (ms).

PRCONNECT_FAIL_BLOCKING_TIME_LINK_CHANGE.description: Time spent blocked in a failed PR_Connect when there has been a link change in the last 60s (ms).

PRCONNECT_FAIL_BLOCKING_TIME_NORMAL.description: Time spent blocked in a failed PR_Connect when we are not shutting down and there has been niether a network nor an offline state change in the last 60s (ms).

PRCONNECT_FAIL_BLOCKING_TIME_OFFLINE.description: Time spent blocked in a failed PR_Connect when the offline state has changed in the last 60s (ms).

PRCONNECT_FAIL_BLOCKING_TIME_SHUTDOWN.description: Time spent blocked in a failed PR_Connect during a shutdown (ms).

FAMILY_SAFETY.description: Status of Family Safety detection and remediation. See nsNSSComponent.cpp.

GEOLOCATION_GETCURRENTPOSITION_VISIBLE.description: This metric is recorded every time a navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition() request gets allowed/fulfilled. A false value is recorded if the owner is not visible according to document.isVisible.

GEOLOCATION_WATCHPOSITION_VISIBLE.description: This metric is recorded every time a navigator.geolocation.watchPosition() request gets allowed/fulfilled. A false value is recorded if the owner is not visible according to document.isVisible.

HTTP_09_INFO.description: HTTP 09 Response Breakdown: lowbit subresource, high bit nonstd port

CONTENT_RESPONSE_DURATION.description: Main thread response times for APZ notifications about input events (ms)

TELEMETRY_SCHEDULER_TICK_EXCEPTION.description: Count of exceptions during executing the TelemetrySession scheduler tick logic.

TELEMETRY_SCHEDULER_WAKEUP.description: Count of TelemetrySession scheduler ticks that were delayed long enough to suspect sleep.

MEDIA_HLS_CANPLAY_REQUESTED.description: Reports a true value when a page requests canPlayType for a HLS media type.

MEDIA_HLS_DECODER_SUCCESS.description: Reports whether a decoder for an HTTP Live Streaming media type was created when requested.

PREDICTOR_PREFETCH_TIME.description: How long it takes from OnStartRequest to OnStopRequest for a prefetch

PREDICTOR_TOTAL_PREFETCHES_USED.description: How many prefetches are actually used by a channel

ADDON_MANAGER_UPGRADE_UI_SHOWN.description: Recorded when the addon manager shows the modal upgrade UI. Should only be recorded once per upgrade.

HTTP_AUTH_TYPE_STATS.description: Recorded once for each HTTP 401 response. The value records the type of authentication and the TLS-enabled status. (0=basic/clear, 1=basic/tls, 2=digest/clear, 3=digest/tls, 4=ntlm/clear, 5=ntlm/tls, 6=negotiate/clear, 7=negotiate/tls)

WEBRTC_CALL_COUNT_2.description: The number of calls made during a session.

FX_CONTENT_CRASH_DUMP_UNAVAILABLE.description: Counts the number of times that about:tabcrashed was unable to find a crash dump.

FX_CONTENT_CRASH_NOT_SUBMITTED.description: Counts the number of times that about:tabcrashed was unloaded without submitting.

FX_CONTENT_CRASH_PRESENTED.description: Counts the number of times that about:tabcrashed appeared and found a crash dump.

VIDEO_PLAY_TIME_MS.description: Total time spent playing video in milliseconds. This reports the total play time for an HTML Media Element whenever it is suspended, such as when the page is unloaded.

VIDEO_UNLOAD_STATE.description: HTML Media Element state when unloading. ended = 0, paused = 1, stalled = 2, seeking = 3, other = 4

SLOW_SCRIPT_NOTIFY_DELAY.description: The difference between the js slow script timeout for content set in prefs and the actual time we waited before displaying the notification (msec).

FULLSCREEN_CHANGE_MS.description: The time content uses to enter/exit fullscreen regardless of fullscreen transition timeout

FULLSCREEN_TRANSITION_BLACK_MS.description: The time spent in the fully-black screen in fullscreen transition

SSL_TLS13_INTOLERANCE_REASON_POST.description: Potential TLS 1.3 intolerance, after considering historical info (see tlsIntoleranceTelemetryBucket() in nsNSSIOLayer.cpp).

SSL_TLS13_INTOLERANCE_REASON_PRE.description: Potential TLS 1.3 intolerance, before considering historical info (see tlsIntoleranceTelemetryBucket() in nsNSSIOLayer.cpp).

FENNEC_READER_VIEW_CACHE_SIZE.description: Total disk space used by items in the reader view cache (KB)

SEARCH_SERVICE_ENGINE_COUNT.description: Recorded once per session near startup: records the search plugin count, including both built-in plugins (including the ones the user has hidden) and user-installed plugins.

SEARCH_RESET_RESULT.description: Result of showing the search reset prompt to the user. 0=restored original default, 1=kept current engine, 2=changed engine, 3=closed the page, 4=opened search settings

FX_STARTUP_MIGRATION_BROWSER_COUNT.description: Number of browsers from which the user could migrate on initial profile migration. Only available on release builds during firstrun.

FX_STARTUP_MIGRATION_EXISTING_DEFAULT_BR.description: The browser that was the default on the initial profile migration. The values correspond to the internal browser ID (see MigrationUtils.jsm)

PRINT_PREVIEW_OPENED_COUNT.description: A counter incremented every time the browser enters print preview.

PRINT_PREVIEW_SIMPLIFY_PAGE_OPENED_COUNT.description: A counter incremented every time the browser enters simplified mode on print preview.

TELEMETRY_PING_SUBMISSION_WAITING_CLIENT.description: The number of pings that were submitted and had to wait for a client id (i.e. before it was cached or loaded from disk)

FX_STARTUP_MIGRATION_AUTOMATED_IMPORT_PR.description: Where automatic migration was attempted, indicates to what degree we succeeded. Values 0-25 indicate progress through the automatic migration sequence, with 25 indicating the migration finished. 26 is only used when the migration produced errors before it finished.

FX_STARTUP_MIGRATION_AUTOMATED_IMPORT_UN.description: Where undo of the automatic migration was attempted, indicates to what degree we succeeded to undo. 0 means we started to undo, 5 means we bailed out from the undo because it was not possible to complete it (there was nothing to undo or the user was signed in to sync). All higher values indicate progression through the undo sequence, with 30 indicating we finished the undo without exceptions in the middle.

TOTAL_CONTAINERS_OPENED.description: Tracking the total number of opened Containers.

UNIQUE_CONTAINERS_OPENED.description: Tracking the unique number of opened Containers.

AUDIOSTREAM_BACKEND_USED.description: The operating system audio back-end used when successfully opening an audio stream, or whether the failure occurred on the first try or not <https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/search?q=AUDIOSTREAM_BACKEND_ID_STR>

WEBVTT_TRACK_KINDS.description: Number of the use of the subtitles kind track. 0=Subtitles, 1=Captions, 2=Descriptions, 3=Chapters, 4=Metadata, 5=Undefined Error

WEBVTT_USED_VTT_CUES.description: Number of the use of the vtt cues.

VIDEO_HIDDEN_PLAY_TIME_MS.description: Total time spent playing video while element is hidden, in milliseconds. This reports the total hidden play time for an HTML Media Element whenever it is suspended, such as when the page is unloaded.

FENNEC_SESSIONSTORE_DAMAGED_SESSION_FILE.description: When restoring tabs on startup, reading from sessionstore.js failed, even though the file exists and is not containing an explicitly empty window.

CONTAINER_USED.description: Records a value each time a builtin container is opened. 1=personal 2=work 3=banking 4=shopping. Does not record usage of user-created containers.

SANDBOX_CONTENT_ENABLED.description: Whether the sandbox is enabled for the content process

SANDBOX_HAS_SECCOMP_BPF.description: Whether the system has seccomp-bpf capability

SANDBOX_HAS_SECCOMP_TSYNC.description: Whether the system has seccomp-bpf thread-sync capability

SANDBOX_HAS_USER_NAMESPACES.description: Whether our process succedeed in creating a user namespace

SANDBOX_HAS_USER_NAMESPACES_PRIVILEGED.description: Whether the system has the capability to create privileged user namespaces

SANDBOX_MEDIA_ENABLED.description: Whether the sandbox is enabled for media/GMP plugins

PRINT_PREVIEW_SIMPLIFY_PAGE_UNAVAILABLE_.description: A counter incremented every time the simplified mode is unavailable on print preview.

APPLICATION_REPUTATION_REMOTE_LOOKUP_TIM.description: Recorded when application reputation remote lookup is performed, `true` is recorded if the lookup times out.

WEAVE_WIPE_SERVER_SUCCEEDED.description: Stores 1 if a wipeServer call succeeded, and 0 if it failed.

GC_PRETENURE_COUNT.description: How many objects groups were selected for pretenuring by a minor GC

FENNEC_SESSIONSTORE_RESTORING_FROM_BACKU.description: When restoring tabs on startup, reading from sessionstore.js failed, but sessionstore.bak was read successfully.

SHARED_WORKER_COUNT.description: Number of the use of SharedWorkers.

DEDICATED_WORKER_SPAWN_GETS_QUEUED.description: Tracking whether a DedicatedWorker spawn gets queued due to hitting max workers per domain limit. File bugs in Core::DOM in case of a Telemetry regression.

DEVTOOLS_TOOLBOX_HOST.description: Records DevTools toolbox host each time the toolbox is opened and when the host is changed (0:Bottom, 1:RIGHT, 2:WINDOW, 3:CUSTOM, 4:LEFT, 5:PAGE, 9:Unknown).

FENNEC_ACTIVITY_STREAM_TOPSITES_LOADER_T.description: Time for the Activity Stream home screen Top Sites query to return (ms)

NUMBER_OF_PROFILES.description: Number of named browser profiles for the current user, as reported by the profile service at startup.

FX_TAB_SWITCH_SPINNER_VISIBLE_LONG_MS.description: Firefox: If the spinner interstitial displays during tab switching, records the time in ms the graphic is visible. This probe is similar to FX_TAB_SWITCH_SPINNER_VISIBLE_MS, but is for truly degenerate cases.

LOAD_INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled for events handling during page load only

SCRIPT_BLOCK_INCORRECT_MIME.description: Whether the script load has a MIME type of ...?  (0=unknown, 1=js, 2=image, 3=audio, 4=video, 5=text/plain, 6=text/csv, 7=text/xml, 8=application/octet-stream, 9=application/xml, 10=text/html, 11=empty)

JS_AOT_USAGE.description: Counts the number of asm.js vs WebAssembly modules instanciations, at the time modules are getting instanciated.

TLS_EARLY_DATA_ACCEPTED.description: TLS early data was used and it was accepted (true) or rejected (false) by the remote host.

TLS_EARLY_DATA_BYTES_WRITTEN.description: Amount of bytes sent using TLS early data at the start of a TLS connection for a given channel.

TLS_EARLY_DATA_NEGOTIATED.description: Sending TLS early data was possible: 0 - not possible, 1 - possible but not used, 2 - possible and used.

VIDEO_AS_CONTENT_SOURCE.description: Usage of a {visible / invisible} video element as the source of {drawImage(), createPattern(), createImageBitmap() and captureStream()} APIs. (0 = ALL_VISIBLE, 1 = ALL_INVISIBLE, 2 = drawImage_VISIBLE, 3 = drawImage_INVISIBLE, 4 = createPattern_VISIBLE, 5 = createPattern_INVISIBLE, 6 = createImageBitmap_VISIBLE, 7 = createImageBitmap_INVISIBLE, 8 = captureStream_VISIBLE, 9 = captureStream_INVISIBLE)

HPACK_BYTES_EVICTED_COMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Number of bytes removed from dynamic table to make room for 1 new item

HPACK_BYTES_EVICTED_DECOMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Number of bytes removed from dynamic table to make room for 1 new item

HPACK_BYTES_EVICTED_RATIO_COMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Ratio of bytes evicted to bytes added (* 100)

HPACK_BYTES_EVICTED_RATIO_DECOMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Ratio of bytes evicted to bytes added (* 100)

HPACK_ELEMENTS_EVICTED_COMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Number of items removed from dynamic table to make room for 1 new item

HPACK_ELEMENTS_EVICTED_DECOMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: Number of items removed from dynamic table to make room for 1 new item

HPACK_PEAK_COUNT_COMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: peak number of items in the dynamic table

HPACK_PEAK_COUNT_DECOMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: peak number of items in the dynamic table

HPACK_PEAK_SIZE_COMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: peak size in bytes of the table

HPACK_PEAK_SIZE_DECOMPRESSOR.description: HPACK: peak size in bytes of the table

MEDIA_DECODING_PROCESS_CRASH.description: Records a value each time GeckoView remote decoding process crashes unexpectedly while decoding media content.

VIDEO_CDM_CREATED.description: Note the type of CDM (0=ClearKey, 1=Primetime, 2=Widevine, 3=unknown) every time we successfully instantiate an EME MediaKeys object.

TELEMETRY_INVALID_PAYLOAD_SUBMITTED.description: Count of individual invalid payloads that were submitted to Telemetry.

MIXED_CONTENT_HSTS_PRIMING.description: How often would blocked mixed content be allowed if HSTS upgrades were allowed, including how often would we send an HSTS priming request? 0=display/no-HSTS, 1=display/HSTS, 2=active/no-HSTS, 3=active/HSTS, 4=display/no-HSTS-priming, 5=display/do-HSTS-priming, 6=active/no-HSTS-priming, 7=active/do-HSTS-priming

MIXED_CONTENT_HSTS_PRIMING_RESULT.description: How often do we get back an HSTS priming result which upgrades the connection to HTTPS? 0=cached (no upgrade), 1=cached (do upgrade), 2=cached (blocked), 3=already upgraded, 4=priming succeeded, 5=priming succeeded (block due to pref), 6=priming succeeded (no upgrade due to pref), 7=priming failed (block), 8=priming failed (accept), 9=timeout (block), 10=timeout (accept)

SSL_SCTS_ORIGIN.description: Origin of Signed Certificate Timestamps received (1=Embedded, 2=TLS handshake extension, 3=Stapled OCSP response)

SSL_SCTS_PER_CONNECTION.description: Histogram of Signed Certificate Timestamps per SSL connection, from all sources (embedded / OCSP Stapling / TLS handshake). Bucket 0 counts the cases when no SCTs were received, or none were extracted due to parsing errors.

SSL_SCTS_VERIFICATION_STATUS.description: Verification status of Signed Certificate Timestamps received (0=Decoding error, 1=Valid SCT, 2=SCT from unknown log, 3=Invalid SCT signature, 4=SCT timestamp is in the future, 5=Valid SCT from a disqualified log)

DOCUMENT_WITH_EXPANDED_PRINCIPAL.description: Number of documents encountered using an expanded principal.

XCTO_NOSNIFF_BLOCK_IMAGE.description: Whether XCTO: nosniff would allow/block an image load? (0=allow, 1=block)

URLCLASSIFIER_VLPS_FILELOAD_TIME.description: Time spent loading Variable-Length PrefixSet from file (ms)

CONTENT_PAINT_TIME.description: Time spent in the paint pipeline for content in milliseconds.

GC_NON_INCREMENTAL_REASON.description: Reason for performing a non-incremental GC (see js::gc::AbortReason)

GC_RESET_REASON.description: Reason for cancelling an ongoing GC (see js::gc::AbortReason)

NARRATE_CONTENT_SPEAKTIME_MS.description: Time in MS that content is narrated in 10 second increments up to 5 minutes

URLCLASSIFIER_VLPS_LOAD_CORRUPT.description: Whether or not a variable-length prefix set loaded from disk is corrupted (true = file corrupted).

FX_STARTUP_MIGRATION_UNDO_OFFERED.description: Indicates we showed a 'would you like to undo this automatic migration?' notification bar. The bucket indicates which nth day we're on (1st/2nd/3rd, by default - 0 would be indicative the pref didn't get set which shouldn't happen). After 3 days on which the notification gets shown, it will get disabled and never shown again.

TABCHILD_PAINT_TIME.description: Time spent painting the contents of a remote browser (ms).

COOKIE_LEAVE_SECURE_ALONE.description: Strict Secure Cookies: 0=blocked secure cookie from http; 1=blocked shadowing secure cookie from http; 2=shadowing secure cookie from https; 3=evicted newer insecure cookie; 4=evicted oldest insecure cookie; 5=evicted secure cookie; 6=evicting secure cookie blocked; 7=blocked downgrading secure cookie from http; 8=downgraded secure cookie from https

TIME_TO_NON_BLANK_PAINT_MS.description: The time between navigation start and the first non-blank paint of a foreground root content document, in milliseconds. This only records documents that were in an active docshell throughout the whole time between navigation start and non-blank paint. The non-blank paint timestamp is taken during display list building and does not include rasterization or compositing of that paint.

TELEMETRY_SEND_FAILURE.description: Time needed (in ms) for a failed send of a Telemetry ping to the servers and getting a reply back.

TELEMETRY_SEND_SUCCESS.description: Time needed (in ms) for a successful send of a Telemetry ping to the servers and getting a reply back.

GPU_PROCESS_LAUNCH_TIME_MS_2.description: GPU process launch time in milliseconds

CONTENT_PROCESS_LAUNCH_TIME_MS.description: Content process launch time until the GetXPCOMProcessAttributes message is received, in milliseconds

TAB_AUDIO_INDICATOR_USED.description: The total usage amount of the operations of tab audio indicator, mute=0 , unmuted=1, unblockByVisitingTab=2, unblockingByClickingIcon=3

TAB_MEDIA_BLOCKING_TIME_MS.description: The time duration from tab's media was blocked to unblocked. Now we record from 1 to 90 seconds, but the record by milliseconds, so the bucket is like [1000ms, 2000ms], [2000ms, 3000ms], e.t.c.

URLCLASSIFIER_COMPLETION_ERROR.description: SafeBrowsing v4 hash completion error (0 = success, 1 = parsing failure, 2 = unknown threat type)

FENNEC_ACTIVITY_STREAM_HIGHLIGHTS_LOADER.description: Time for the Activity Stream highlights query to return (ms)

FX_PREFERENCES_CATEGORY_OPENED.description: Count how often each preference category is opened.

FENNEC_LOOP_OTHER_LATENCY.description: Latency in microseconds of non-UI events in the Android event loop between posting and processing

FENNEC_LOOP_UI_LATENCY.description: Latency in microseconds of UI events in the Android event loop between posting and processing

PAGE_MAX_SCROLL_Y.description: Maximum distance in CSS pixels a user scrolls down the vertical axis of the root frame of a page. This doesn't include any scrolling of nested scroll frames such as inputs, iframes, or scrollable divs.

TOTAL_SCROLL_Y.description: Count of the total number of CSS pixels scrolled up or down in the vertical axis of the root frame of all the pages visited in a subsession. This doesn't include any scrolling of nested scroll frames such as inputs, iframes, or scrollable divs.

GPU_PROCESS_INITIALIZATION_TIME_MS.description: GPU process initialization (excluding XPCOM and fork time) time in milliseconds

SPDY_CONTINUED_HEADERS.description: Size of continued H2 headers in bytes.

FENNEC_ORBOT_INSTALLED.description: Whether or not users have Orbot installed

CSP_REFERRER_DIRECTIVE.description: Whether a document with a CSP policy (report-only or enforcing) contains a referrer directive ('true') or not ('false').

FILE_EMBEDDED_SERVICEWORKERS.description: Count ServiceWorkers that are embedded in pages loading with the file:/// protocol.

NETWORK_CONNECTION_COUNT.description: Number of the use of navigator.connection.

BUSY_TAB_ABANDONED.description: Records a value each time a tab that is showing the loading throbber is interrupted. Desktop only.

URLCLASSIFIER_VLPS_CONSTRUCT_TIME.description: Time spent constructing Variable-Length PrefixSet from file (ms)

VIDEO_AS_CONTENT_SOURCE_IN_TREE_OR_NOT.description: Usage of an invisible {in tree / not in tree} video element as the source of {drawImage(), createPattern(), createImageBitmap() and captureStream()} APIs. (0 = ALL_IN_TREE, 1 = ALL_NOT_IN_TREE, 2 = drawImage_IN_TREE, 3 = drawImage_NOT_IN_TREE, 4 = createPattern_IN_TREE, 5 = createPattern_NOT_IN_TREE, 6 = createImageBitmap_IN_TREE, 7 = createImageBitmap_NOT_IN_TREE, 8 = captureStream_IN_TREE, 9 = captureStream_NOT_IN_TREE)

Cache wins: 41-50 for 1-100ms, 51-59 for 101-1000ms, 60-68 for 1-10s, 69-73 for 11-60s and 74 for > 1m. Network wins: 39-30 for 1-100ms, 29-21 for 101-1000ms, 20-12 for 1-10s, 11-7 for 11-60s and 6 for > 1m.

TIME_TO_FIRST_CLICK_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_INTERACTION_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next click, key, mouse or scroll event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_KEY_INPUT_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next key event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next mouse move event per top-level content browsing context.

TIME_TO_FIRST_SCROLL_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from the first non-blank paint to the creation time of the next scroll event per top-level content browsing context.

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to be aborted due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down).

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to complete, given that it failed.

WEBRTC_DTLS_CLIENT_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a client DTLS handshake to complete, given that DTLS succeeded.

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to be aborted due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down).

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to complete, given that it failed.

WEBRTC_DTLS_SERVER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for a server DTLS handshake to complete, given that DTLS succeeded.

SSL_HANDSHAKE_RESULT.description: SSL handshake result, 0=success, 1-255=NSS error offset, 256-511=SEC error offset + 256, 512-639=NSPR error offset + 512, 640-670=PKIX error, 671=unknown err

AUSHELPER_CPU_ERROR_CODE.description: The error code from the aushelper system add-on when querying the registry for CPU information for bug 1296630 (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

AUSHELPER_CPU_RESULT_CODE.description: Whether the system is affected by bug 1296630 (1=No, 2=Yes, 3=Error, and 4=Unknown).

AUSHELPER_WEBSENSE_ERROR_CODE.description: The error code from the aushelper system add-on when gathering information on Websense (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

AUSHELPER_WEBSENSE_REG_EXISTS.description: Whether the system has a Websense InstallVersion registry value (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).

URLCLASSIFIER_NEGATIVE_CACHE_DURATION.description: Negative cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider

URLCLASSIFIER_POSITIVE_CACHE_DURATION.description: Positive cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider

SSL_CT_POLICY_COMPLIANCE_OF_EV_CERTS.description: Certificate Transparency Policy compliance of successfully established SSL connections with EV certificate (1=Compliant, 2=Insufficient number of SCTs, 3=Insufficient diversity of CT Log operators)

SSL_CT_POLICY_COMPLIANT_CONNECTIONS_BY_C.description: Number of successfully established TLS connections compliant with the Certificate Transparency Policy, by CA. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/security/manager/ssl/RootHashes.inc for names of CAs. Bucket zero holds CAs not present in the list.

SSL_CT_POLICY_NON_COMPLIANT_CONNECTIONS_.description: Number of successfully established TLS connections NOT compliant with the Certificate Transparency Policy, by CA. See https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/security/manager/ssl/RootHashes.inc for names of CAs. Bucket zero holds CAs not present in the list.

URLCLASSIFIER_MATCH_RESULT.description: The result of each URL lookup against both google and google4 lists. (0 = no match, 1 = V2 prefix only, 2 = V4 prefix only, 3 = V2 and V4 prefixes, 4 = V2 and V4 completions, 5 = V2 completion only, 6 = V4 completion only, 7 = V2 completion and v4 prefix, 8 = V2 prefix and V4 completion, 9 = unexpected result)

APPLICATION_REPUTATION_ALLOWLIST_MATCH.description: For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of the allow list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)

APPLICATION_REPUTATION_BLOCKLIST_MATCH.description: For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of block list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_DURATION.description: Duration of animations running on the compositor in milliseconds

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_MAX_LAYER_AREA.description: High-watermark of layer area affected during a compositor animation. Units are layer pixels squared.

FENNEC_SESSIONSTORE_ALL_FILES_DAMAGED.description: Both the main session file and its backup could not be read and and the first run pref is false.

EXTENSION_INSTALL_PROMPT_RESULT.description: Results of displaying add-on installation notifications.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to abort ICE due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down). Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to complete ICE, given that it failed. Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_ANSWERER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the answerer to complete ICE, given that ICE succeeded.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_ABORT_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to abort ICE due to some external factor (eg; PeerConnection torn down). Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_FAILURE_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to complete ICE, given that it failed. Does not count cases where StartChecks() was never called.

WEBRTC_ICE_OFFERER_SUCCESS_TIME.description: The length of time (in milliseconds) it took for the offerer to complete ICE, given that ICE succeeded.

FX_TAB_SWITCH_SPINNER_TYPE.description: Firefox: If the spinner interstitial displays during tab switching, record if the tab being switched to has been seen (content was visible) before. If not, record if the tab is 'old' (> 1000ms since creation) or 'new'.

JS_PRIVILEGED_PARSER_COMPILE_LAZY_AFTER_.description: Time elapsed between the moment a function is lazy-parsed (end of parsing of the ScriptSource) and the moment it is recompiled as non-lazy (start of compilation), in milliseconds, for privileged code.

JS_WEB_PARSER_COMPILE_LAZY_AFTER_MS.description: Time elapsed between the moment a function is lazy-parsed (end of parsing of the ScriptSource) and the moment it is recompiled as non-lazy (start of compilation), in milliseconds, for web code.

DEVTOOLS_DOM_OPENED_COUNT.description: Number of times the DevTools DOM Inspector has been opened.

DEVTOOLS_DOM_TIME_ACTIVE_SECONDS.description: How long has the DOM inspector been active (seconds)

FEED_PROTOCOL_USAGE.description: Usage counts of feed protocols used to load a page. (1=feed, 2=feed:http, 3=feed:https, 4=feed:brokenScheme, 5=pcast, 6=pcast:http, 7=pcast:https, 8=pcast:brokenScheme)

FX_TAB_CLOSE_PERMIT_UNLOAD_TIME_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken to run permitUnload on a browser during tab close to see whether or not we're allowed to close the tab (ms).

FX_TAB_CLOSE_TIME_ANIM_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken from the point of closing a tab (with animation), to the browser element being removed from the DOM. (ms).

FX_TAB_CLOSE_TIME_NO_ANIM_MS.description: Firefox: Time taken from the point of closing a tab (without animation) to the browser element being removed from the DOM. (ms).

IMAGE_ANIMATED_DECODE_ON_DRAW_LATENCY.description: Time from starting a decode of an animated image to it showing up on the screen (us)

IMAGE_ANIMATED_DECODE_TIME.description: Time spent decoding an animated image (us)

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_MAX_CONTIGUOUS_DROP.description: For APZ/scrolling compositor animations, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered
For compositor animations of chrome-process layers, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered
For compositor animations of content-process layers, the maximum number of contiguous frame drops encountered

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_APZ.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for APZ/scrolling animations in the compositor.

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_CHROME.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for compositor animations of chrome-process layers.

COMPOSITOR_ANIMATION_THROUGHPUT_CONTENT.description: Frame throughput ratio (scaled up to 1000) for compositor animations of content-process layers.

HTTP_ONSTART_SUSPEND_TOTAL_TIME.description: Time in milliseconds that http channel spent suspended between AsyncOpen and OnStartRequest.

FX_PREFERENCES_CATEGORY_OPENED_V2.description: Count how often each preference category is opened.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled mouse move event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_TOUCH_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled touch move event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_APZ_WHEEL_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled wheel event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_CLICK_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse click event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

INPUT_EVENT_QUEUED_KEYBOARD_MS.description: Time (ms) for the keyboard event to dispatch, but before handlers executing.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_FRAME_.description: The number of pixels of the frame for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_PERCEN.description: The ratio of the frame size (in total number of pixels) to the relative limit (~viewport size plus some tolerance factor, typically 12.5% in each dimension, i.e. ~27% tolerance in total area) for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor expressed as a percentage (e.g. 130 = frame area was 30% larger than the relative limit)

DISPLAY_ITEM_USAGE_COUNT.description: Count of which layout display items are being created. Display items are created by layout to determine what content to render. A full description is above the class definition for nsDisplayItem. The list of types is kept in nsDisplayItemTypes.h.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_DISMISSED.description: Update: the dismiss action was executed for this application update doorhanger type.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_MAIN_ACTION_DOORHANG.description: Update: the main update action was initiated for this application update doorhanger type.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_MAIN_ACTION_MENU.description: Update: the update action was initiated from the PanelUI application update menu item.

UPDATE_NOTIFICATION_SHOWN.description: Update: the application update doorhanger type that was displayed.

URLCLASSIFIER_MATCH_THREAT_TYPE_RESULT.description: Whether or not a full URL match is of the same threat type on V2 and V4. (0 = same, otherwise the value is a bit flag where 0x01 = V2 phishing, 0x02 = V2 malware, 0x04 = V2 unwanted, 0x08 = V4 phishing, 0x10 = V4 malware, 0x20 = V4 unwanted)

FX_SEARCHBAR_SELECTED_RESULT_METHOD.description: The input method the user used to select a result in the searchbar. 'enter' => The user hit the Enter key without choosing a result in the popup. 'enterSelection' => The user chose a result and then hit the Enter key. 'click' => The user clicked a result with the mouse.

FX_URLBAR_SELECTED_RESULT_METHOD.description: The input method the user used to select a result in the urlbar. 'enter' => The user hit the Enter key on the heuristic result at index 0. 'enterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result (in exotic ways) and then hit the Enter key. 'click' => The user clicked a result with the mouse. 'arrowEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using arrow keys and then hit the Enter key. 'tabEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using tab at least once and then hit the Enter key. 'rightClickEnter' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using right click and then hit the Enter key.

GPU_PROCESS_CRASH_FALLBACKS.description: Count how often we use different fallbacks when the GPU process crashes: None=0, GPUProcessDecodingDisabled=1, GPUProcessDisabled=2

TIME_TO_DOM_COMPLETE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domComplete.

TIME_TO_DOM_CONTENT_LOADED_END_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domContentLoadedEventEnd.

TIME_TO_DOM_CONTENT_LOADED_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domContentLoadedEventStart.

TIME_TO_DOM_INTERACTIVE_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domInteractive.

TIME_TO_DOM_LOADING_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to domLoading.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_END_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to loadEventEnd.

TIME_TO_LOAD_EVENT_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to loadEventStart.

TIME_TO_RESPONSE_START_MS.description: Time in milliseconds from navigationStart to responseStart.

FORM_ISINDEX_USED.description: Whether there has been an isindex form submission in this session.

DISPLAY_SCALING.description: Scaling percentage for the display where the first window is opened

BOX_ALIGN_PROPS_IN_BLOCKS_FLAG.description: Whether we have layed out any display:block containers with not-yet-supported properties from CSS Box Align.

INPUT_EVENT_RESPONSE_COALESCED_MS.description: Time (ms) from the Input event being created to the end of it being handled, but with overlapping events coalesced.

MEDIA_EME_SECURE_CONTEXT.description: Reports whether a navigator.requestMediaKeySystemAccess() was called in a secure context (i.e. on an origin served over HTTPS) or not.

APZ_AWARE_KEY_LISTENERS.description: The percentage of pages with a non-passive key event on the path to the root scrolling element that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.

APZ_AWARE_MOUSEMOVE_LISTENERS.description: The percentage of pages with a mousemove listener anywhere in the document that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.

FX_SESSION_RESTORE_PRIVACY_LEVEL.description: Session restore: The privacy level chosen by the user (0: Collect data from all sites, 1: Collect data only from non-HTTPS sites, 2: Collect no data)

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_USAGE.description: Whether we raced network with the cache. (0=network & no racing, 1=cache & no racing, 2=network & raced, 3=cache & raced, 4=network & delayed race, 5=cache & delayed race)

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_MOUSE_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled mouse move event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_TOUCH_MOVE_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled touch move event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_APZ_WHEEL_MS.description: Time (ms) for the APZ handled wheel event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_KEYBOARD_MS.description: Time (ms) for the keyboard event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_MOUSE_DOWN_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse down event spent in handlers.

INPUT_EVENT_HANDLED_MOUSE_UP_MS.description: Time (ms) for the mouse up event spent in handlers.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_BG_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the background and the script is not on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_BG_TRACKING_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the background and the script is on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_FG_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the foreground and the script is not on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

TIMEOUT_EXECUTION_FG_TRACKING_MS.description: Time in ms used to execute callbacks from setTimeout/setInterval, when the script belongs to a tab in the foreground and the script is on the tracking list. Multiple events are aggregated over a 1s interval.

CONTENT_JS_BACKGROUND_TICK_DELAY_TOTAL_M.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is completely in the background. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

CONTENT_JS_FOREGROUND_TICK_DELAY_TOTAL_M.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup that is (partially) in the foreground. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

CONTENT_JS_KNOWN_TICK_DELAY_MS.description: Time (in ms) that a pending vsync gets delayed by a runnable associated with a TabGroup when the vsync event's timestamp is before the starting time of the runnable. The time is measured from the vsync event's time stamp to when the runnable finishes execution.

TCP_FAST_OPEN.description: When a http connection is closed, track whether or not TCP Fast Open was used: 0=TFO_NOT_TRIED, 1=TFO_TRIED_NEGOTIATING, 2=TFO_DATA_SENT, 3=TFO_FAILED.

HTTP_AUTH_DIALOG_STATS_2.description: Stats about what kind of resource requested http authentication. (29=top-level doc, 30=same origin subresources, 31=same origin xhr, (nsIContentPolicy type)=cross-origin subresources per nsIContentPolicy type)

IPC_MESSAGE_SIZE2.description: Measures the size of all IPC messages sent that are >= 4096 bytes.

ASYNC_ANIMATION_FRAME_SIZE.description: The number of pixels of the frame each time we potentially run a transform animation on the compositor. Intended for comparison with ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_FRAME_SIZE.

FX_PREFERENCES_OPENED_VIA.description: Count how the Preferences are opened.

URLCLASSIFIER_VLPS_LONG_PREFIXES.description: Length of the first 20 long prefixes (> 4 bytes) received in a Safe Browsing V4 table during an update.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_OCEC_ON_.description: Time in milliseconds between onStartRequest from the cache and onCacheEntryCheck. Report only when net wins and OCEC is before onStartRequest from net.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_WITH_NETWORK_SAVED_TI.description: Time in milliseconds that we saved when we race cache with network.

TIME_BETWEEN_UNLABELED_RUNNABLES_MS.description: Every time we run an unlabeled runnable, this histogram records the time (in ms) since the last unlabeled runnable ran.

NETWORK_RACE_CACHE_BANDWITH_NOT_RACE.description: Amount of bytes received when we decide not to race cache with network.
