corroborate.omnijar_corrupted.description: Whether the omni jar (omni.ja) was found to be missing or corrupt when checked during startup.

corroborate.system_addons_corrupted.description: Whether any system add-on (XPI files) were found to be missing or corrupt when checked during startup.

telemetry.ecosystem_new_send_time.description: The timestamp im milliseconds of the last time we tried to send an Ecosystem ping

telemetry.ecosystem_old_send_time.description: The timestamp im milliseconds of the last time we tried to send an Ecosystem ping

startup.is_cold.description: Whether or not this startup is the first startup since OS reboot (according to our best guess.)

devtools.inspector.node_selection_count.description: Number of times a different node is marked as selected in the Inspector regardless of the cause: context menu, manual selection in markup view, etc.

pdf.viewer.fallback_shown.description: How many times PDF Viewer fallback bar was shown.

pdf.viewer.print.description: How many times PDF Viewer print functionality was used.

pdf.viewer.used.description: How many times PDF Viewer was used.

blocklist.lastModified_rs_addons.description: Keep track of the last time the "addons" remotesetting blocklist has been successfully updated (as a datetime string in UTC format), set to "Missing Date" when the timestamp couldn't be retrieved.

blocklist.lastModified_rs_plugins.description: Keep track of the last time the "plugins" remotesetting blocklist has been successfully updated (as a datetime string in UTC format), set to "Missing Date" when the timestamp couldn't be retrieved.

blocklist.lastModified_xml.description: Keep track of the lastupdate datetime from a successfully loaded xml blocklist, set to "Invalid Date" or "Missing Date" when the timestamp is invalid or missing. (based on the lastupdate attribute set on the XML document element, converted from a milliseconds timestamp into a datetime string in UTC format).

blocklist.useXML.description: Keep track of the currently enabled blocklist engine (set to false if the remote settings blocklist is the one enabled).

os.environment.is_admin_without_uac.description: Indicates that the process is lauched with Admin privileges but without UAC.

firstStartup.statusCode.description: Status of the FirstRun service, which runs post-install/early-startup in Firefox.

pwmgr.potentially_breached_passwords.description: The number of potentially breached passwords, as determined by LoginBreaches.getPotentialBreachesByLoginGUID.

contentblocking.trackers_blocked_count.description: A count of the number of tracking events blocked.

webrtc.hostnameobfuscation.disabled_fail.description: The number of times the connection failed with hostname obfuscation disabled. Hostname obfuscation uses mDNS addresses to prevent browser fingerprinting by using WebRTC to collect local IP addresses.

webrtc.hostnameobfuscation.disabled_succ.description: The number of times the connection succeeded with hostname obfuscation disabled. Hostname obfuscation uses mDNS addresses to prevent browser fingerprinting by using WebRTC to collect local IP addresses.

webrtc.hostnameobfuscation.enabled_faile.description: The number of times the connection failed with hostname obfuscation enabled. Hostname obfuscation uses mDNS addresses to prevent browser fingerprinting by using WebRTC to collect local IP addresses.

webrtc.hostnameobfuscation.enabled_succe.description: The number of times the connection succeeded with hostname obfuscation enabled. Hostname obfuscation uses mDNS addresses to prevent browser fingerprinting by using WebRTC to collect local IP addresses.

browser.searchinit.engines_cache_corrupt.description: Whether the list of engines in the search cache was found to be corrupt during initialization.

update.fix_permissions_attempted.description: Set when we attempt to fix update directory permissions.

firstStartup.elapsed.description: Number of milliseconds the FirstRun service took to run.

a11y.backplate.description: Boolean tracking if the user has the backplate preference enabled or disabled.

security.tls_delegated_credentials_txn.description: Count of how many transactions used delegated credentials (ietf-draft-tls-subcerts)

networking.ftp_opened_channels_files.description: Number of FTP channels opened for files.

networking.ftp_opened_channels_listings.description: Number of FTP channels opened for directory listings.

datasanitization.network_cookie_lifetime.description: This scalar reports the value of the network.cookie.lifetimePolicy pref.

datasanitization.privacy_clearOnShutdown.description: A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.cache pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.cookies pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.downloads pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.formdata pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.history pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.offlineApps pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.openWindows pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.sessions pref.
A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.clearOnShutdown.siteSettings pref.

datasanitization.privacy_sanitize_saniti.description: A boolean reporting the value of the privacy.sanitize.sanitizeOnShutdown pref.

datasanitization.session_permission_exce.description: A count of how many "session" cookie exceptions a user has set.

gfx.adapter.description.description: Long form description of the Graphics adapter

gfx.adapter.driver_files.description: List of graphics adapter driver files

gfx.compositor.description: Name of the graphics compositor in use. possible values are "opengl, d3d11, client, webrender or basic"

gfx.display.count.description: Number of displays connected to the device

gfx.display.primary_height.description: Height of the primary display, takes device rotation into account.

gfx.display.primary_width.description: Width of the primary display, takes device rotation into account.

gfx.headless.description: Boolean indicated whether graphics is running in headless (no display) mode

gfx.adapter.device_id_last_seen.description: Graphics adapter device identification This is a temporary workaround for some early telemetry system issues. See Bug 1601091 for more information

gfx.compositor_last_seen.description: Name of the graphics compositor in use. possible values are "opengl, d3d11, client, webrender or basic". This is a temporary workaround for some early telemetry system issues. See Bug 1601091 for more information

deletion.request.impression_id.description: An identifier used by user interaction pings in Pocket/newtab and Messaging System.

fxrPC.isFirstRun.description: Determine if this user is first time to run Firefox Reality PC.

a11y.sitezoom.description: Boolean tracking if the user has the site-specific zoom enabled or disabled.

widget.dark_mode.description: Whether the OS theme is dark.

policies.count.description: A uint with the number of active enterprise policies, collected once at startup.

corroborate.omnijar_mismatch.description: Whether the build IDs of the omni jar (omni.ja) and libxul do not match.

gecko.build_id.description: The build id of the Gecko engine, example: '20200205124310'. It contains the time the build was created and is used as a unique id for the build.

gecko.version.description: The version of the Gecko engine, example: '74.0a1'. It consists of the major and minor version, followed by the release life cycle phase. 'a' stands for alpha or nightly, 'b' stands for beta. The number behind the release life cycle phase indicates minor releases within the phase.

qm.repositories_initialization_time.description: A temporary probe to track the time for initializing the best-effort repositories especially the longest the time.

timestamps.first_paint_two.description: Record the timestamp of the first main window paint, in milliseconds since process start. Intended to replace first_paint since first_paint is broken.

browser.startup.action.description: The action that the user took with the slow startup notification bar. 0: No action (default) 1: User chose to open SUMO document on slow startup 2: User chose to never show the notification bar again 3: User dismissed the notification bar

browser.startup.average_time.description: The average startup time computed by the slow startup notification bar in milliseconds.

browser.startup.recorded_time.description: The startup time computed by the slow startup notification bar in milliseconds.

browser.startup.slow_startup_notificatio.description: Whether the slow startup notification bar is disabled for the user.

browser.startup.slow_startup_notified.description: Whether the slow startup notification bar was shown to the user during this session.

browser.startup.too_new_for_notification.description: Whether the slow startup notification bar was suppressed because the profile is too new.

gfx.os_compositor.description: Boolean indicating whether the os compositor is being used by WebRender. Only collected in the first subsession.

browser.input.touch_event_count.description: Windows only. Counts occurrences of touch events, measured when user starts a touch event.

networking.loading_certs_task.description: The time in milliseconds to load any external certificates. This occurs off of the main-thread, but can block main-thread operations.

networking.nss_initialization.description: The time in milliseconds to initialize the NSS component in the parent process.

security.https_only_mode_enabled.description: Measures user retention of the HTTPS-Only Mode. 0 = never enabled, 1 = enabled, 2 = disabled (but was enabled)

telemetry.failed_late_write.description: The number of times a late write stack failed to be parsed.

deletion.request.sync_device_id.description: An identifier used by sync ping, to identify the current Firefox profile for a specific Account.

blocklist.lastModified_rs_addons_mlbf.description: Keep track of the last time the "addons-bloomfilters" remotesetting blocklist has been successfully updated (as a datetime string in UTC format), set to "Missing Date" when the timestamp couldn't be retrieved.

blocklist.mlbf_enabled.description: Keep track of whether the addons blocklist engine uses bloom filters (blocklist v3). If false, the blocklist v2 is used instead.

blocklist.mlbf_generation_time.description: Keep track of the generation time of the addon blocklist's bloom filter. This marks the point in time until which signed add-ons are recognized by the selected bloom filter from the addons-bloomfilters collection. The value is a datetime string in UTC format, or  "Missing Date" when unavailable.

blocklist.mlbf_stash_time_newest.description: Keep track of the timestamp of the most recent stash of the addons blocklist. Only meaningful when mlbf_enabled and mlbf_stashes are true. The value is a datetime string in UTC format, or "Missing Date" when unavailable.

blocklist.mlbf_stash_time_oldest.description: Keep track of the timestamp of the oldest stash of the addons blocklist. Only meaningful when mlbf_enabled and mlbf_stashes are true. The value is a datetime string in UTC format, or "Missing Date" when unavailable.

blocklist.mlbf_stashes.description: Keep track of whether the bloomfilter-based blocklist engine uses stashes from the addons-bloomfilters collection, together with an infrequently updated base bloomfilter. If false, the latest (full) bloom filter is downloaded on every update of the addon blocklist. This metric is only meaningful if mlbf_enabled is true.

migration.uninstaller_profile_refresh.description: Set when a profile refresh is initiated from the uninstaller.

findbar.find_next.description: The count of how many times the find next button was used per session.

findbar.find_prev.description: The count of how many times the find previous button was used per session.

findbar.highlight_all.description: The count of how many times the "Highlight All" button was used in find toolbar.

findbar.match_case.description: The count of how many times the "Match Case" button was used in find toolbar.

findbar.match_diacritics.description: The count of how many times the "Match Diacritics" button was used in find toolbar.

findbar.shown.description: The count of how many times the "Find toolbar" was shown per session.

findbar.whole_words.description: The count of how many times the "Whole Words" button was used in find toolbar.

downloads.file_opened.description: The count of how many times files were opened from the download panel.

downloads.panel_shown.description: The count of how many times the downloads panel was shown per session.

fullscreen.used.description: The number of times that a session enters browser fullscreen (f11-fullscreen).

browser.startup.abouthome_cache_result.description:
How the about:home startup cache functioned on startup.
0: Result value was never set (error case) 1: Cache did not exist 2: Cache page stream was corrupt / inaccessible 3: Cache script stream was corrupt / inaccessible 4: Cache was invalidated by a version bump 5: Cache was valid, but read too late to be useful. 6: Cache was valid and used. 7: Cache is disabled. 8: User did not load about:home on its own by default. 9: Cache is disabled because about:newtab preloading is disabled.

browser.startup.abouthome_cache_shutdown.description: True if the about:home startup cache was written via the AsyncShutdown blocker.

security.https_only_mode_enabled_pbm.description: Measures user retention of the HTTPS-Only Mode in Private Browsing. 0 = https-only never enabled in PBM, 1 = https-only enabled in PBM, 2 = https-only disabled in PBM (but was enabled)

fog.eval.user_active.description: Whether the user is presently actively interacting with Firefox. For use in evaluating baseline engagement for Project FOG.

fog.eval.user_active_error.description: How many Telemetry stopwatch errors did we have while trying to measure user activity? These could be attempts to start a started timer or finish an unstarted timer or so forth. See Stopwatch::Start and Stopwatch::Finish for details. For use in evaluating baseline engagement for Project FOG.

fog.eval.window_raised.description: Whether a Firefox window is presently raised. For use in evaluating baseline engagement for Project FOG.

fog.eval.window_raised_error.description: How many Telemetry stopwatch errors did we have while trying to measure window raising? These could be attempts to start a started timer or finish an unstarted timer or so forth. See Stopwatch::Start and Stopwatch::Finish for details. For use in evaluating baseline engagement for Project FOG.

browser.searchinit.init_result_status_co.description: Status code (nsresult) for the search service initialization routine. Stored as a string due to issues with large uint scalars when the scalar was created.

networking.http3_enabled.description: True if HTTP3 is enabled at the start of a session.

deletion.request.ecosystem_client_id.description: An identifier used by the ecosystem ping, to delete all ecosystem metrics collected from this profile if the user opts out of telemetry.

formautofill.creditCards.autofill_profil.description: Count at store time how many credit card autofill profiles user has.

js.run_time_us.description: How many microseconds we spent in running user code in SpiderMonkey, including JavaScript code and WebAssembly code.

startup.seconds_since_last_os_restart.description: The time in seconds between the first browser window loading, and the time the OS started. This can give us an indication of whether starting the browser may have been the first thing the user did after starting their computer.

wasm.compile_time_baseline_us.description: How many microseconds we spent in the baseline WebAssembly compiler.

wasm.compile_time_cranelift_us.description: How many microseconds we spent in the Cranelift WebAssembly compiler.

wasm.compile_time_ion_us.description: How many microseconds we spent in the IonMonkey WebAssembly compiler.

browser.engagement.profile_count.description: The count of the browser profiles on the current system. This counts profiles that have been used across all OS user accounts on machine since this probe was added. The value persists across installs. A value of 0 is reported if there is an error determining the correct count.

devtools.markup.scrollable.badge.clicked.description: Number of times the scrollable inspector badge has been clicked.

gfx.linux_window_protocol.description: Windowing protocol on Linux. Can be Wayland, WaylandDRM, XWayland, or X11

fog.eval.user_inactive_error.description: How many Telemetry stopwatch errors did we have while trying to measure user inactivity? These could be attempts to start a started timer or finish an unstarted timer or so forth. See Stopwatch::Start and Stopwatch::Finish for details. For use in evaluating baseline engagement for Project FOG.

printing.dialog_opened_via_preview_tm.description: A counter incremented every time a user opens the system print dialog from the print preview interface.

printing.dialog_via_preview_cancelled_tm.description: A counter incremented every time a user cancels a system print dialog that they opened from the print preview interface.

printing.preview_cancelled_tm.description: A counter incremented every time a user exits print preview without printing.

printing.preview_opened_tm.description: A counter incremented every time a user opens print preview.

os.environment.allowed_app_sources.description: Indicates what sources the OS is currently configured to allow apps to be installed from. Possible values are "Anywhere", "Recommendations", "PreferStore", "StoreOnly", "NoSuchFeature", or "Error". "Recommendations" allows installs from anywhere, but recommends a comparable app from the store, if available. "NoSuchFeature" will be reported on versions of Windows that do not have an app source setting.

media.element_in_page_count.description: The number of times a document hierarchy contained at least one HTMLMediaElement. In addition, the telemetry probe 'MIXED_CONTENT_UNBLOCK_COUNTER' records the total number of loaded top level content documents, which can help us calculate the result of the percentage of documents using media.

widget.gtk_theme_has_scrollbar_buttons.description: Whether the active Gtk theme has scrollbar buttons.

additionalProperties.description: Generic histogram to track uptake of remote content like blocklists, settings or updates.
Generic histogram to track uptake of remote content like blocklists, settings or updates.

The count of attempted accumulations to unknown histogram keys for histograms that restrict the set of allowed keys ('keys' property). The names of the offending histograms are used as keys in this probe.
The counts of events recorded in the process, category, method, and object of the key, even if event recording for the category was not enabled.
The count of attempted accumulations to unknown scalar keys for scalars that restrict the set of allowed keys ('keys' property). The names of the offending scalars are used as keys in this probe.

browser.usage.graphite.description: The number of times a graphite2 font has been loaded.

telemetry.discarded.accumulations.description: Number of discarded accumulations to histograms in child processes

telemetry.discarded.child_events.description: Number of discarded events in child processes

telemetry.discarded.keyed_accumulations.description: Number of discarded accumulations to keyed histograms in child processes

telemetry.discarded.keyed_scalar_actions.description: Number of discarded actions on keyed scalars in child processes

telemetry.discarded.scalar_actions.description: Number of discarded actions on scalars in child processes

telemetry.profile_directory_scans.description: The number of times a profile directory scan was initiated in ProfileAge.jsm

slowSQL.description: Slow SQL queries for both the main and other threads. The execution of an SQL statement is considered slow if it takes 50ms or more on the main thread or 100ms or more on other threads. Slow SQL statements will be automatically trimmed to 1000 characters.

additional_properties.description: A JSON string containing any payload properties not present in the schema

document_id.description: The document ID specified in the URI when the client sent this message

geo.description: Results of a geographic lookup based on the client's IP address

db_version.description: The specific geo database version used for this lookup

subdivision1.description: First major country subdivision, typically a state, province, or county

subdivision2.description: Second major country subdivision; not applicable for most countries

header.description: Headers included in the client's HTTP request

isp.description: Results of ISP lookup based on the client's IP address

db_version.description: The specific geo ISP database version used for this lookup

name.description: The name of the ISP associated with the client's IP address

organization.description: The name of a specific business entity associated with the client's IP address when available; otherwise the ISP name

uri.description: Components of the URI to which this ping was sent

user_agent.description: Parsed components of the client's user agent string

normalized_app_name.description: Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized app name

normalized_channel.description: Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized channel name

normalized_os.description: Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized OS name

sample_id.description: Hashed version of client_id (if present) useful for partitioning; ranges from 0 to 99

submission_timestamp.description: Time when the ingestion edge server accepted this message
